title: beef stew over rice
directions: Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in melted butter until lightly brown. Add dry ingredients, then add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over meat.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 5 minutes and remove from heat; add 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour this over 2 gallons popped popcorn.
Spread out in a shallow pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
After cooking, pour out onto wax paper to cool.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk for 8 minutes; pour over Marshmallow Creme and chocolate chips.
Beat with electric mixer until it starts to thicken and has dull look.
Add nuts; pour into buttered pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: madge's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions in oil until lightly brown.
Mix remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour in skillet.
This can be used on baked or grilled chicken.
Excellent on ribs and chops!

title: crock-pot quail or rabbit
directions: Dip meat in egg batter and roll in flour.
Brown in skillet with Crisco.
Place chopped onion and bell pepper in bottom of crock-pot.
Cover with water.
Turn on high.

title: hot chili dip
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt together chili and cream cheese; stir to blend.
Serve with chips.

title: quick sherbet
directions: Soften sherbet and thaw strawberries.
Combine.
Add bananas and re-freeze.
This is so refreshing.

title: chess pie cookie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix sugars and flour.
Add to beaten eggs.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over baked pastry.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: jewish cake
directions: Whip eggs in saucepan; add brown sugar and mix well.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar melts.
Mix with flour; add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ground beef patties
directions: Make ground beef into small patties and fry in skillet.
When patties are done, pour excess grease off and discard.
Mix mushroom soup with water.
Pour over patties.
Let come to a boil and they are done.

title: giant oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together first seven ingredients.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; gradually add dry ingredients, beating until well blended.
Stir in oats, pecans and raisins.
Drop by 1/4 cup on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: corn sausage bake
directions: Cook sausage in skillet over low heat. Drain. Mix soup and milk. Stir in crumbled crackers. Layer cracker mixture, corn and sausage in casserole dish, having top layer corn and sausage. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cocoa.
Melt butter.
Add milk and stir.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir and pour on buttered dish.

title: *custard cheese pita
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: california beans
directions: Put all ingredients into slow cooker for several hours, then serve.

title: banana split bars
directions: Puree bananas.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add bananas, pineapple, eggs, oil and vanilla. Also nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in cherries.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Spread with a white frosting.
Makes 36 bars.

title: spiced peaches
directions: You will need 1 spice bag or cheesecloth.
Combine all ingredients.

title: ann's millionaire's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 baked graham cracker crusts.
Chill thoroughly, at least 6 hours or overnight. Serves 16.

title: white pizza
directions: Liberally brush entire pizza shell with olive oil.
Sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder to taste.
Layer tomatoes, onions, pepper and olives.
Top with the cheeses.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Cut green beans into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until tender, then rinse in cold water.
Combine beans and next 4 ingredients. Combine vinegar and next 5 ingredients in a small non-aluminum saucepan.
Place over medium heat and cook for 5 minutes, until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over beans; toss gently. Cover and chill overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: blowout cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat peanut butter and butter until fluffy.
Add sugars; beat until light and smooth.
Add egg; beat 3 minutes.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture and beat thoroughly. Sprinkle milk over mixture.
Beat to soften dough.
Fold in chocolate chips, peanuts, then add candy carefully.
Drop 2 tablespoon clumps onto ungreased baking sheet, leaving 1 inch space for spreading.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until just browned.
Makes about 30.

title: venison hasenpfeffer
directions: Soak the meat for 2 days in a solution of water, vinegar, sliced onions, melted butter, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Wipe the meat dry and brown it in a Dutch oven in hot butter.
Add about 1 cup of the soaking solution.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
When almost ready to serve, add 1/2 cup red cooking wine and 1 cup sour cream.
Stir well and turn the meat in it several times.
Serve with cabbage or egg noodles.

title: venison meatballs
directions: Crumble bread slices coarsely; combine with milk and baking powder and let stand five minutes.
Add venison, onion, salt and seasoned salt and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Brown.
Place in baking dish.
Combine soups with evaporated milk.
Pour over meatballs and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salsa
directions: Brown sausage. Drain grease. Combine meat and onion. Cook until onion is tender. Add all other items and heat until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bean salad
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Pour mixture over beans and mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight.

title: beleta's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together and blend well.
Add milk.
Cook on medium-low heat until candy forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Cool candy, then add butter and peanut butter.
Mix and pour into buttered dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: basic pudding mix
directions: Sift all ingredients together and store in a tightly covered container in a cool place.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all together. Add ginger ale just before serving. Add coloring for different colors, green or pink lemonade and red food coloring. Can make ice cubes out of lemonade and apricot nectar for color.

title: no bake chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a deep pan; heat until margarine is melted and mixed all together.
Boil for 1 minute, then add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir until coated. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Wait 30 minutes to cool and harden.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients at a rolling boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off of heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir just until candy starts to thicken.
(It sets up fast.)
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix and bake all in the same pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, vinegar, water and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: In a large bowl dump all ingredients, except brown gravy mix. This is not easy to mix with spoon, but is easier to combine all ingredients with hand.
Form into hamburger patties.
Place in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes.
Mix brown gravy in bowl and pour over patties, allowing to cook about 15 minutes more. Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: showboat pork and beans
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Mix in other ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or reduce barbecue sauce to 1/2 cup and simmer in crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix water and mustard in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Whisk in cheese sauce from pouch.
Stir in dry pasta; cover with tight fitting lid.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover; stir in sour cream.
Continue baking, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lazy person cake
directions: Spread pineapple (undrained) in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread pie filling on top of pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix on top of pie filling.
Top with nuts.
Slice margarine in thin slices and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until brown.

title: "seems healthy" meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into a loaf and bake at 350° for one and one-half hours.

title: ellonore's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Great for vegetables or chips.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together, then add oil, eggs, walnuts and vanilla.
Sift together salt, soda, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well with apple mixture and add raisins.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Wash broccoli; trim and dry.
In pan, cook broccoli in butter until soft.
Blend in flour and simmer until smooth and bubbly. Add next 8 ingredients.
Stir constantly until thick and smooth. Remove and blend (may be frozen at this point with the cream and egg yolks added later).
Stir in cream and bring just to a boil. Beat yolks and add a small amount of soup mix to it.
Return it all to the pot and serve.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Mix Jiffy cornbread mix, eggs and milk.
Add cheese, onion and broccoli.
Melt margarine and pour in mixture.
Spray skillet with Pam and cook at 450° until done.

title: stromboli
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage and pizza sauce in crock pot. Let cook until heated through and through.
Spread butter on both sides of hoagies buns and place on cookie sheet.
Add cheese. Place in heated oven until cheese and butter is melted. Serve meat mixture on top of hoagie buns.

title: tapioca dessert
directions: Boil water and salt.
Add tapioca.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 15 minutes or until clear.
Add sugar and Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool overnight.
Next day, add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Stir well to mix.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Combine salt, sugar, mustard and vinegar in saucepan and heat to boiling point.
Pour over sliced cucumbers in jars and seal. This makes an extra tangy pickle.

title: oatmeal meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Pack firmly into ungreased loaf pan.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, brown sugar, oats, raisins, walnuts and chocolate pieces.
Stir in oil, water and vanilla. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets (cookies will spread).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.
Let stand for about 1 minute.
Carefully remove to wire racks to cool.
Store airtight.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: savory crescent chicken
directions: Blend soft cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add other ingredients and mix. Separate crescent rolls into squares (2 together). Roll slightly, then spoon mixture on center of dough. Pull up 4 corners of dough to center and seal. Repeat until all 4 bundles are done. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden. Serve with sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix hamburger and onion together.
Run tortillas under hot water.
Spray baking dish with no stick spray.
Place a tablespoon of meat and onion into each tortilla and roll.
Place into pan. Pour chili over rolled tortilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and the last 5 minutes spread cheese over top and melt.

title: blue ribbon banana nut cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and beat.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to mixture.
Beat real good.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in greased baking dish or pan, about 8-inch square, at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in a 3-quart bowl.
Add water or milk.
Let soak until bread is soft.
Mix with a spoon.
Add eggs, sugar, baking powder, nutmeg and vanilla; beat well.
Grease and flour pan.
May add 1 cup raisins, chopped apples, cooked prunes or sliced peaches.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour, then at 350° for another 1/2 hour.
Bake until knife inserted in middle comes out clean. Pudding swells, but falls as it cools.

title: bluegrass pie
directions: Combine all ingredients into a medium mixing bowl; mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pie is set.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Grease 10-inch Bundt pan. Sprinkle pan with 1 tablespoon of sugar mixture. Combine remaining ingredients and mix until smooth. Pour 1/2 mixture into pan, sprinkle remaining sugar on this batter. Top with remaining batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool 15 minutes and invert onto cake plate.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Boil ingredients 10 minutes.
Pour over 4 pounds shaved ham. Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
One hour before, warm in oven at 250°.
Great for a crowd.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Spoon out in a well-greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding mix, powdered sugar and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Place crackers in bottom of pan.
Put half of mixture in pan, then layer of crackers, then rest of mixture.
Add crackers to top.
Spread frosting on top and chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix flour and salt together and then mix with butter and margarine until evenly distributed.
Add enough ice water to make a ball.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Prick top with fork.
Bake at 250° until very lightly browned.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix
together the first 3 ingredients.	Set aside.
Mix the next 3 ingredients, then combine with first ingredients.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy and marshmallows.
Add sugar and condensed milk and heat until dissolved.
Put in container.
Add homogenized milk to fill line.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Peel peaches and slice into a greased pan (8 x 8). Trim crust of bread. Cut each slice into 4 fingers. Place over peaches. Mix oleos, flour, egg and sugar. Pour over top of bread. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small strips or chunks.
Marinate approximately 4 skinless, boneless chicken breasts in approximately 1/2 to 1 cup of vegetable oil, lemon juice and chopped green onions.
Put in glass baking dish (9 x 13-inch). Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Beat 2 eggs in water and set aside.
Divide sausage into 6 portions.
Wrap one portion around each boiled egg and seal well. Dip into egg and water mixture, then into bread crumbs.
(You can refrigerate overnight.)
Drop eggs into deep oil heated to 375°. Cook about 9 to 10 minutes.
Serve with gravy.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a large bowl in the order given up to and including the onion.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Spread Miracle Whip over top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with foil and chill overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and let congeal.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, pecans, coconut, raisins, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: la dolice lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add sauce.
Place half of noodles in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the cottage cheese, half of the Mozzarella cheese and half of meat mixture. Repeat layers and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: oven french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Dip bread slices in and put on 2 greased jelly roll pans.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Put
1 can pork and beans in bottom of	2-quart
casserole. Mix brown sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle 1/2	of
mixture on beans. Put other can of beans in casserole.
Sprinkle rest of
sugar and mustard mixture on.
Put bacon on and
top	with catsup.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: french quarter steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak; cut steak into serving-sizes. Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Dredge steak in flour mixture; reserve excess flour mixture.

title: golden blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring well.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with flour mixture, stirring just to combine.
Fold in berries.
Spoon batter in greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Chill for 3 hours.
Shape in balls and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown. Spoon off fat.
Combine soup, milk and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top each chicken piece with lemon slice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.
Serve over rice.

title: country barbecue ribs(microwave)
directions: Cut ribs into 1-inch pieces.
Arrange in a 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) baking dish; place larger pieces around edge.
Cook, covered with waxed paper, for 12 minutes, or until partially cooked, rearranging halfway through cooking time.
(For conventional oven, you cook on rack, meaty side up, about 30 minutes in a 400° oven.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain liquid from one can of asparagus.
Place asparagus in casserole.
Cover with one can of soup.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Repeat layer with asparagus, soup, crackers and cheese.
Pour liquid from one can of asparagus over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can make half of recipe.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Using a heavy-duty mixer, mix water, shortening and milk until smooth.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute.
Stop mixer; mix 15 minutes on medium speed.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour until doubled in size.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Put in greased oven pan. Brush butter on top.
Let rise again for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Brush butter on top again.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Spoon refried beans and 3 cups Cheddar cheese into centers of tortillas; roll tortillas to enclose filling.
Place seam side down in 3-quart rectangular glass dish.
Top with chili. Microwave on High for 14 to 16 minutes or until heated through, turning dish once.
Sprinkle with remaining cup cheese.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: new year's eve lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight in water covering lentils.
Brown beef and onion in oil.
Add water; cook until meat falls apart.
Drain lentils and add.
Cook for about 2 hours or more, stirring occasionally.
Also can add grated carrot and celery.
Add salt and pepper and more water, if needed.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim off fat.
Semi-freeze meat and slice with the grain, making strips about 1/4-inch thick.
Place meat in tightly sealed container.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over meat. Marinate overnight, turning upside-down several times.

title: curry mayonnaise
directions: While broccoli is cooking to just tender stage, mix the curry and garlic powders into mayonnaise which has been thinned with lemon juice.
A delightful complement to broccoli!

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Preheat grill, slice potatoes into 6 to 8 pieces each.
Place potato wedges onto open aluminum foil sections; top with onions. Sprinkle with dill, salt and pepper to taste.
Top each with a slice of butter.
Fold over top of aluminum foil loosely and crease, then fold up ends of foil.
Place on medium-hot grill. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Check one packet after 8 minutes.
If the potatoes are not lightly browned, cook longer.
Potatoes taste best when slightly browned.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Make a day ahead.

title: phoebe's fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with mixer until soft creamy.
Add marshmallow cream.
Add orange juice and grated peel.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve as a dip with fresh strawberries, pineapple chunks, sliced bananas (soak in lemon juice), sliced apple (red) and red and green seedless grapes.
Great for parties, picnics and teas.

title: fried walnuts
directions: In large saucepan over high heat, bring 6 cups water to boil. Add walnuts; cook 1 minute.
Rinse under running hot water (drain well).
In large bowl, toss nuts in sugar.
Use deep skillet. Heat 1-inch of oil to 350°.
With slotted spoon, place nuts in coarse sieve to drain.
Sprinkle with salt.
Toss lightly to keep from sticking.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container to keep fresh.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Mix all ingredients (except oleo) in covered bowl.
Put in greased tube pan.
Pour stick of melted oleo over dough.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into walnut sized balls. Flatten with floured glass.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes.
Do not grease cookie sheet.

title: kim's lasagne
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook meat until browned. Add onion and garlic; cook 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, water and basil.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine Ricotta, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups sauce into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top half the uncooked lasagna, all Ricotta mixture, 1 cup Mozzarella, 1/2 c. Parmesan, 1 1/2 cups sauce and remaining lasagne.
Top with remaining sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover for 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add water and cook just until thick.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix flour mixture together.
Place half of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with rhubarb mixture, then cover with remaining flour mixture. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hidden valley ranch crescent rolls
directions: Separate dough. Cut in half lengthwise to make 16 crescent rolls.
Beat egg yolk with water.
Brush on dough.
Sprinkle with dressing mix.
Roll up in crescent shapes.
Brush with egg mixture.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in preheated 375 degree oven for 11 - 13 minutes.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: congealed asparagus salad
directions: Soften gelatin in asparagus liquid; dissolve gelatin mixture in boiled water.
Add lemon juice, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Allow to cool.
Fold in celery, onion, pimiento, asparagus (cut into 1-inch pieces) and pecans.
Allow to congeal and serve.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Layer 4 cups chopped rhubarb in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour over rhubarb, sugar, then Jell-O (dry) and cake mix (dry).
Melt oleo and pour over cake mix.
Pour 1 cup of water over oleo.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream or ice cream.

title: green beans and potatoes greek style
directions: In large pot, saute onion in olive oil until transparent.
Add the green beans and potatoes, that have been quartered, then cut in half.
Add the tomato sauce and water.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before eating.
Great with fresh veggies.

title: rebecca salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, jello and cottage cheese.
Mix well, then stir in all other ingredients.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and cheese. Slowly add sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in egg yolk.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well. Chill thoroughly.
Shape in small balls.
Press cherry lightly on dough to flatten. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken rubin
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana wrap
directions: Spread peanut butter and jelly on warm tortilla.
Place banana near tight edge of the tortilla.
Fold up the bottom fourth of the tortilla.
Bring the right edge over the banana and roll up.

title: rice casserole
directions: Simmer together the butter, onion and celery.
Add soups, mushrooms and rice.
Bake at 325°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare one package of Dream Whip.
Mix into peanut butter. Add cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.

title: lemon meringue cake
directions: Combine ingredients through lemon rind.
Bake in two cake pans in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Then spread lemon curd between layers.
Beat egg whites, warm water, and cream of tartar on medium high adding sugar 1 tablespoon at a time.
Cover cake with meringue and bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes then put in refrigerator till it cools completely.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine melted butter and crumbs.
Press on bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and butter in mixer on high speed for 15 minutes.
Pour in pan.
In layers, add bananas, pineapple, whipped cream, nuts and cherries.
Cover and chill overnight.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Soften margarine; add flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Mix into a crumbly mixture.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture and press remainder of mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine butter, cola and marshmallows in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat and cook until marshmallows are melted.
Stir occasionally.

title: crescents(portuguese)
directions: Cream the butter and add other ingredients.
Shape them.
Put them on buttered cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Cool and roll in granulated sugar or confectioners sugar.
Preparation time:
45 minutes.

title: frozen rocky road
directions: In a small saucepan, combine milk, sugar and chocolate. Bring to boiling over low heat, stirring constantly (flecks of chocolate may be visible).

title: scallop kabobs italian style
directions: Wrap scallop with a strip of ham.
Place in skillet.
Cook with all ingredients.
Great on the grill skewered.

title: half and half
directions: Chill both, then mix equal parts into punch bowl.
Add crushed or cubed ice.

title: cheese onion pastries
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheese and onions.
Separate dough into 16 triangles cutting each diagonally in half.
Place rounded teaspoon of cheese mixture on center of each triangle and bring corners to center over filling; overlap edges and press to seal. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with oil and sprinkle with dill weed.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 13 minutes. Can be prepared 2 hours ahead, then cook if you keep chilled in the refrigerator.

title: white bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and add flour and knead. Let raise until double in bulk, about 1 hour. Shape into two loaves and place in greased loaf pans. Let raise until double in bulk. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine flour and next 4 ingredients together in a large bowl. In a separate bowl, mix together egg, juice, water and melted butter.
Make a well in the flour mixture and pour egg mixture into it.
Just moisten dry ingredients.
Fold in prepared cranberries and walnuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: alternate of rum cake - chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter cake mix, chocolate pudding mix, eggs and oil.
Add mixed flavorings and add water to make 1 cup.
Mix.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Add coconut in the bottom of pan.
Add mixture and bake 1 hour.

title: piccalilli
directions: Chop and mix together the green tomatoes, cabbage, onions, peppers and salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: broccoli-cheese chowder
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add onions, potatoes, salt and pepper. Bring to boiling again and boil for 10 minutes.

title: economy cake
directions: Mix water, sugar, butter, and raisins in a pot and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
When cool enough to not burn, add soda.
This will foam.
Add salt, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, and flour.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350 degree oven until the cake pulls loose from the sides of the pan or inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate peanut fudge
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Toast the peanuts on a baking sheet in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 6 to 7 minutes. Remove the peanuts from the oven and set aside until needed.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Fresh strawberries (halved), blueberries, grapes, mandarin oranges, etc., may be used.
Be sure all fruit is well drained.

title: west point sandwiches
directions: Cut rolls lengthwise.
Mix butter, onion, mustard and sauce together. Spread on top half of rolls.
Place ham and cheese on bottom half.
Put back in pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: old fashioned beef stew aux fine herbs
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add seasonings, celery and water.
Simmer over low heat for 2 hours.
Add remaining vegetables and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: r f spezziello salad(i used shell macaroni when the above is not available.)
directions: Mix well.
Makes large salad; freezes well.
If more moisture needed, add more Cool Whip.
Decorate top with maraschino cherries.

title: confederate cannonballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into 1-inch size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature, then grate.
Boil macaroni until tender; drain and rinse thoroughly with cold water. Layer macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper in a greased casserole dish.
Blend egg and milk together and pour mixture over second layer of macaroni and cheese.
Place about 3 pats of butter on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: herbed pork medallions
directions: Cut pork into 1/2 inch slices and pound to flatten. Combine butter and garlic powder; brush over pork. Combine seasonings; sprinkle over pork. Place the two greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pans. Broil 4-6 inches from heat for 5 minutes; turn and broil 3 minutes longer. Brush with honey; broil for 1 minute or until meat juices run clear. Serves 6.

title: yogurt dip for fruit
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit.

title: ruth's cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage. Run cold water over cabbage. In pot add water, oil and rest of seasoning.
Stir.
Add cabbage.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes.
Do not stir.
Turn cabbage from bottom to top. Cover and continue to cook to desired doneness.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's mush
directions: Crumble the cornbread up in a saucepan. Mix enough milk to make a mixture about like ordinary mush. Heat and let thicken some; serve with butter or with milk.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup milk, mix well. Add well beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Add other 1/2 cup milk. Cook on medium-high heat and stir constantly.
Cook until thickens. Remove from heat, but do not turn heat off.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir in well.
Return to heat and turn off immediately. Remove from heat when mixture stops bubbling.
Top with meringue and brown lightly.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars in bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, and baking soda.
Add to shortening mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Add 1/2 stick margarine and cubed cheese. Mix lightly.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add crumbled crackers.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk.
Combine dry ingredients and add.
Beat well.
Add mashed bananas and nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Let butter soften to room temperature.
Use a fork to mix sugar, butter and Crisco together very thoroughly.
Start with a mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Start adding flour and milk, alternating, mixing well. Add flavoring last, then use a spoon to mix walnuts in last. Start with cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour tomatoes
directions: Fry potatoes and onion in a small amount of oil in a large frypan (or use a nonstick coated frypan sprayed with vegetable spray) until they are almost tender.
Spread potatoes over bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Using the same pan, lightly saute zucchini slices a few minutes.
Zucchini should be tender-crisp, not soft.
Layer zucchini on top of potatoes.
Distribute shredded cheese evenly over zucchini.
Using blender or whisk, mix milk, eggs, mustard, salt and Worcestershire sauce together; pour mixture over potatoes, zucchini and cheese.
Sprinkle fresh minced parsley or chives and paprika generously over top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 30 to 45 minutes (eggs should be "set" and lightly browned).
Cut into squares to serve.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed.
Let cool completely.
Then break into pieces and place in a large glass bowl.
Then make pudding and pour over brownies.
Next sprinkle with shaved chocolate or chocolate chips.
Then cover chocolate with Cool Whip.
Last, drizzle chocolate syrup over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: alphabet vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery; drain fat.
Add liquids; bring to boil.
Add frozen vegetables; bring to boil.
Add parsley or basil and pasta.
Simmer for 10 minutes, or until pasta is al dente.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Mix together.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250° or 300°.
Stir after about 2 1/2 hours.

title: carrot oatmeal muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add the brown sugar, milk, egg and margarine.
Mix thoroughly.
Add carrots and oats; mix well. Spoon the batter into greased muffin pan cups, filling 2/3 full. Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients. Add sausage and put into a 9 x 13-inch flat casserole dish.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes with foil covering.
Take off foil for the last 10 minutes.
Enjoy!!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mildred's kolackies
directions: In bowl place melted shortening and cool milk; add next 8 ingredients, stirring well after each.
Finally, add flour 1 cup at a time until a soft dough can be kneaded to a smoothness. Allow to double in shape.
Punch down and form round disks and allow to raise.
Fill a center finger dent with jelly of your choice and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: betty brownie cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a bowl and set aside.
Combine 2 sticks oleo, water and 3 1/2 teaspoons of cocoa in a saucepan and cook to a boil, then pour over flour mixture; blend well.
Mix 1/2 cup buttermilk, salt, eggs and soda into mixture and pour into a greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: wacky no cholesterol cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Add oil, vanilla, vinegar and water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange carrots
directions: Sprinkle carrots with brown sugar substitute.
Spoon frozen orange juice over the carrots.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: pasta pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pasta, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and butter; toss.
Press into buttered 9-inch pie plate or 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and oregano; mix well.
Spoon meat mixture over pasta.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup (remaining) Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese (1 cup).
Return to oven just to melt cheese.
Garnish with green pepper.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix melted butter, softened cheese and pepper.
Add flour and roll fairly thin.
Cut.
Cook in slow oven 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Prepare and beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar: beat until combined.
(DO NOT OVERBEAT.) Stir in chocolate chips, cover and chill in refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll into ball and cover with plastic wrap.
Just before serving roll into pecans.
Serve with chocolate graham crackers.

title: meringue bars
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Mix in egg yolks until crumbly and press in greased pan.

title: nancy's brownies
directions: Melt 4 squares chocolate and 1/2 pound butter together.
Beat together the sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour.
Add chocolate mixture and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch(good!)
directions: Crush cranberry.
Beat in water with egg beater.
Add apple juice, cinnamon and cloves. Simmer 5 minutes. Add orange juice. Serve hot.

title: nutty cream cheese frosting(italian cream cake)
directions: Place pecans in a shallow pan; bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until toasted.
Stir occasionally; cool.
Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla at medium speed until creamy.
Add sugar, beating at low until blended.
Beat at high speed until smooth; stir in pecans.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Place enough water in a pan so that it will cover shrimp.
Add seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp; boil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; let stand 15 minutes.
The longer it stands, the spicier it will be.
Drain.
Pack in ice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Peel, eat and enjoy.

title: crawfish lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Blend 2 sticks butter and flour; add 3 cartons whipping cream and Romano cheese.
Put aside.

title: mexican green bean casserole
directions: Save 1/2 can Durkee French fried onions back.
Mix all other ingredients together with the other 1/2 of Durkee French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Top with remaining French fried onions and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli-cheese stuffed shells
directions: In a medium bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons filling into cooked shell.
In an 8-inch square baking dish, spread evenly over bottom.
Arrange shells in single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Add extra green onions.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans 2 hours in 2 quarts water in large kettle.
Bring to boil quickly; simmer until tender.
Drain beans, reserving water. Fill bean pot with half the beans; add onion and remaining beans. Press pork deep into beans until surface is level.
Combine salt, mustard, pepper, molasses and 3/4 cup boiling water; pour over beans.
Pour reserved water to top of bean pot; cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Remove cover; bake for 1 hour longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, egg and vanilla. Blend in sugar and milk.
Add other dry ingredients.
Mix well. Chill until firm.
Roll thin and cut with floured cutters.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Yield: 16 servings.
Pan Size: 10-inch Bundt.

title: corn pone
directions: Cream shortening, eggs, and sugar together. Continue to beat alternately adding combined dry ingredients and milk.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: ham bar-b-cue
directions: Cook onion in oleo and drain, then add rest of ingredients. Simmer until hot.
Add meat and heat.

title: slaw for a crowd
directions: Place cabbage, onions, bell pepper and pimentos in a gallon jar.
In a saucepan, combine last 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over top 4 ingredients already in a gallon jar.
When cool, let stand in refrigerator at least 12 hours before serving. This will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.
Serves approximately 20 people.

title: bobby knight's coconut cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, oil, water, 1 cup coconut, eggs and 1 cup cream of coconut together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fast homemade corn oat bread
directions: Heat milk, oil, brown sugar and salt in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add ice cubes, then stir in yeast.
Add flour, cornmeal and oatmeal.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed sweet bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, poppy seeds, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, combine eggs, milk, cooking oil, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Combine wet and dry ingredients until just moistened.

title: quick enchiladas
directions: Layer floured tortillas in large baking pan, alternate layering tortillas, onions, meat and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Mix in dry ingredients alternately with the sour milk to which the baking soda has been added.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs with milk.
Layer ingredients, except eggs.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fantisico salsa
directions: Place onion, peppers, garlic, salt and pepper in blender until smooth.
Add drained tomatoes and cumino and blend until well mixed.
You may serve right from the blender or cook mixture on stove 5 minutes, just until it comes to a boil.
Serve with corn chips.
Great for a party.

title: the greatest barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients; bring to a boil, then simmer until proper consistency, up to one hour.
"The result is the sauce!"

title: party punch
directions: Mix juices and fruit together but hold the sherbet until ready to serve.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Grate cheese.
Place half of cheese on bottom of pan.
Drain can of chilies, reserving the liquid.
Dice the chilies small and sprinkle over the one layer of cheese.
Sprinkle remaining half of cheese over chilies.
Thoroughly beat eggs, using the liquid from the chilies.
Pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into small squares and serve.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Wash and drain peppers, then devein and remove seeds (unless you like it really hot).
Set aside.
Grate cheese; stuff peppers. Then add rest of cheese to sausage and biscuit mix.
Mix well; set aside.

title: creamed celery
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine in a large skillet for 10 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle flour over vegetables; blend in, then add chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and bubbles (3 minutes).
Stir in pepper, Worcestershire sauce and cream and heat slowly, stirring just until hot.
Spoon into bowl; sprinkle with almonds.
Serves six.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscotch chips. Pour in peanuts and noodles.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice pickles and onion into a large bowl.
Next pour the salt over the pickles and onions.
Mix occasionally.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Now in a large pot, boil the sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to a rolling boil and place the pickles and onion in the pot.
When the mixture is turning yellow, it is done.
Put in sterilized jars.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: In bowl, mix cream cheese first, then add Cool Whip and other ingredients.
Let chill overnight or at least 5 hours.
Then put your choice of fruit on top.

title: potato planks
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until tender; cut lengthwise into eighths.
Set oven to broil.
Place potatoes, cut side down, in ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Brush with oil.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle potatoes with half the mixture.
Broil potatoes about 3 inches from heat until potatoes begin to bubble slightly, about 10 minutes.
Turn; brush with oil and sprinkle with remaining salt mixture.
Broil until golden brown and tender, about 5 minutes longer.

title: american mushroom sauce
directions: Mix everything in small bowl.
Serve over cooked vegetables or pasta.

title: bob's favorite wheaties cookies(gail dickhausen's dad, bob olson.)
directions: Blend shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add vanilla and flour, sifted with soda and salt.
Stir in Wheaties, coconut and nuts. Form into round balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Beat for two minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Batter will be very thin. Bake at 350° until cake tests done, about 45 minutes.
When cool. Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: peaches and cream crescent dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 2 long rectangles. Place in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan; press in bottom of pan, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
In a small bowl, blend cream cheese, sugar and almond extract; mix until smooth.
Spread over dough.
Spoon pie filling evenly over cream cheese mixture. In a medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and margarine; mix until crumbly.
Stir in pecans; sprinkle crumb mixture over fruit. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into serving size pieces.
Top each serving with Cool Whip and a few chopped pecans.
Also great cold.

title: low-fat dip
directions: Toast bread crumbs in oven at 350° until barely golden brown. Crush the cardamon seed and crack the black pepper.
Mix with the bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Steam the broccoli; drain but do not let it cool.
Arrange on a platter.

title: kachumbari(india)
directions: Chop all ingredients well.
Mix.
Salt to taste.
Serve as a relish with stews, curries, grilled meat, etc.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 10 to 15 minutes.

title: basic baked beans
directions: Day before serving:
Soak beans in cold water, covered, overnight (water should cover beans completely).

title: easy punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add 7-Up and sherbet when ready to serve.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Place thawed berries, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and salt in large bowl.
Beat for 15 minutes on medium speed until stiff. Whip cream with vanilla.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Pile into baked pie shell.
Freeze overnight.
(Very good summer dessert.)

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water the chips and sugar.
Heat until morsels melt and mix is smooth. Remove from heat; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter; mix well.
Put firmly in 9-inch spring-form pan, covering bottom and up sides; set aside.

title: chalupa
directions: Place beans, pork roast, water, onion, garlic, seasonings, chilies and pimentos in heavy kettle and simmer 5 hours or until roast is tender.
Remove roast and break with fork.
Return to bean pot; cook uncovered until thick, about 1/2 hour.
Serve over corn chips.
Pass condiments for choice of toppings such as diced tomato, diced avocado, sliced green onion, grated Cheddar cheese, sour cream, chopped olives, etc.
Serve with hot or medium pepper sauce.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Blend in milk and flavoring.
Stir in flour, cherries and pecans.
Divide dough into 2 pieces.
Form each piece into a "log" about 8 inches long.
Roll each section of dough in the flaked coconut.
Wrap each section in waxed paper or Saran Wrap.
Chill overnight.
Cut in 1-inch slices and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: raisin nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes to partially cool.
Add salt, raisins and nuts and blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Chill.
Wrap and pack.

title: pork roast marinade
directions: Mix well.
Put roast in plastic bag, pour sauce over and marinate 2 to 3 hours turning occasionally.
May be marinated overnight.

title: poor man's baked cubed steak
directions: Mix together the hamburger, milk and cracker crumbs.
Pat down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut 3 across times 5 down.
Flour and brown.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour the cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup water over hamburger mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all cake ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 3 layers.

title: coconut cake
directions: Whip cream; add sugar and flour. Mix egg yolks and vanilla. Fold in egg whites (do not stir). Pour into three 9-inch cake pans that are lightly greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. After baked, poke holes in cake and pour coconut milk over layers. When cake has cooled, cover with frosting.

title: taco dip
directions: Heat oven to 350° or use microwave.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread on bottom chili, then spread sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Heat until melted.
Dip your chip and enjoy!

title: blueberry and wild rice breakfast for 2(traditional indian breakfast, chippewa)
directions: Spoon wild rice and blueberries into two bowls.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Pour cream over.
Serve.

title: lentil soup
directions: Serve with dill pickles and hot bread

title: date and nut squares
directions: Cream
first
3 ingredients;
alternate with applesauce and mix in dry ingredients.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325°
for
1 hour.	Sprinkle powdered sugar on top and cut into desired size squares.

title: ginger-honey glaze
directions: Combine honey, lemon or lime juice, and ginger.
Mix. Chill. Makes 1/2 cup glaze.

title: orange rhubarb drink
directions: In saucepan, cook rhubarb with water and sugar for 20 minutes. Press through a sieve.
Put fruit juices in jar.
Add mixture; cover and chill.

title: rum and raisin loaf
directions: Mix raisins and rum in bowl.
Set aside.
Stir 1 teaspoon sugar in warm milk and sprinkle with yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes or until the surface is frothy.
Stir gently to moisten any dry particles remaining to top.
Sift flour and salt into large bowl. Melt butter, cool slightly.
In medium bowl, mix remaining sugar, butter, eggs, and lemon peel.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Pour into flour mixture, combining to make a soft dough.
On floured surface, knead dough 5 to 10 minutes until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size-about 30 minutes. Grease loaf pan. Knead raisin and rum mixture into a loaf shape and place in greased loaf pan.
Let stand in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush loaf with egg yolk.
Bake 40-45 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.

title: mock mincemeat
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook until well done and seal.

title: chicken moumba
directions: Saute chicken in chicken fat (or butter or oil).
Remove chicken and saute onion; add flour, peanut butter and water. Return chicken to pan.
Cover and cook on low for 45 minutes. Serve with baked or boiled potatoes, sweet potatoes or rice.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Heat oven to
Mix
pie
filling	and cherries in ungreased square baking dish 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Spread evenly. Mix baking mix,
nuts,	sugar
and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle	dry
mixture
over
cherries.
Bake until brown, approximately 35 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday sparkle
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whir until blended. Garnish as desired.
Makes 1 serving.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into a ball and roll in confectioners sugar or candy beads.

title: zesty bacon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill at least 2 hours. Serve with pretzel chips.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with Cool Whip until well dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the vegetables, Miracle Whip and cheese together.
Place in pan.
Mix butter and crushed crackers together.
Place on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked grits
directions: Heat milk; add butter and grits.
Stir until smooth, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot appetizer cookies
directions: Cream oleo and cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix with hands.
Divide into 4 rolls and put in wax paper.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice and bake at 350°.
Watch.

title: cafe cappuccino
directions: Mix ahead and store in airtight jar.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Fry ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into casserole dish and bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry crust.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with waxed paper.
Lightly grease and flour waxed paper.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli; add onions, olives, salt and pepper. Mix well. Add dressing and top with bacon bits.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash into large pieces.
Boil until tender; drain and mash (leaving some chunks).
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Add additional buttered bread crumbs on top and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend oil, pumpkin, eggs and water in blender.
Add walnuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice in bowl; mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture; mix well.
Combine milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add to batter; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes. Turn onto cake plate.

title: chicken and sausage
directions: Cook sausage in oil until brown.
Remove from pan.
Add chicken and stir until cooked.
Remove from pan.
Pour out drippings, leaving 1 tablespoon.
Add garlic and saute.
Add wine and broth. Stir until boiling.
Add drained peppers, oregano and rosemary. Boil until thickened, approximately 10 minutes.
Whisk in butter, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Stir in sausage and chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over noodles.

title: cheddar sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add peppers and onions; cook until tender. Stir in cheese snack and tomatoes.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Fill buns with meat mixture.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt. Add melted butter and chocolate.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pasties
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco shortening; add flour and salt. Mix well.
Will be consistency of cookie dough.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour before using.

title: sausage pilaf
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Brown sausage.
Add celery, onion and pepper; stir and cook until tender.
Stir in soup and rice.
Place in casserole; bake at 250° for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until meat falls off bones.
Pick chicken and divide in half.
Save 2 soup cans of chicken broth.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 chicken, cream of chicken soup (spread thin over chicken), 1/2 of chicken, cream of celery soup (spread thin over chicken).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs from Stove Top mix. Sprinkle evenly the seasoning package.
Pour 2 cans of chicken broth over top.
Make sure the bread crumbs are moist.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Hollow out one loaf of bread, cut extra bread in cubes for dipping.
Cut second loaf of rye bread in cubes.
Place mixture in hollowed bread.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo or butter.
Boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries.
Mix with sugar; let set 30 minutes, then mix rest.
Chill and serve.

title: chugwater chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain excess fat.
Saute onion with meat. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns or French (any chili powder can be used).

title: asparagus side dish
directions: Mix asparagus with onion and wine.
Heat butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add asparagus; spread well over skillet.
Let come to boil once, stirring occasionally.
Season with lemon juice, salt and nutmeg.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Beat the ingredients together.
Cook in double boiler until thick (stir constantly if not using double boiler).
Remove from stove.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk.

title: ginger-kissed carrots
directions: In saucepot over medium-high heat, cook carrots in boiling water 4 minutes or until tender; drain.
In the meantime, in skillet over medium-high heat, cook scallion in oil 1 minute.
Add orange juice, soy sauce, brown sugar and ginger; bring to a boil. Add carrots.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes more or until sauce thickens and carrots are heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in coconut, chopped dates and shredded zucchini; mix well.
Put into a 10 x 15-inch greased pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion soup mix well and place in 9 x 13 pan.
Lay chicken parts on top.	Sprinkle with Lipton dry onion soup mix on the top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: candied yams
directions: Place yams or sweet potatoes in baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes. Cover pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clyde's chili
directions: Mix chili powder and flour.
Brown meat in large skillet or heavy pan.
Add flour mixture while browning.
When brown, add remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly for two hours.

title: chicken, sausage, peppers and potatoes
directions: Cook all ingredients, except potatoes.
Season with all spices. Add potatoes.
Toss.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Feeds 4 to 6.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Mix juice, flour and sugar and pour over layered cheese and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ginger's breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble. Drain well.
Sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mushrooms and mustard; mix well and pour over sausage. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes if desired when served.

title: play clay
directions: I admit I made a mistake.

title: fresh apple-pecan pound cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until thoroughly combined.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples, pecans and raisins. Turn into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Slice crust off of bread and flatten with a rolling pin.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place asparagus on bread and roll up.
Dip in melted margarine and place on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with more cheese and bake until crisp at 350°.

title: real corn cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch or slightly smaller baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm, puffy in appearance.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Mix together soup, milk, green chilies and onion.
Place 1 cup crushed Doritos in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Next put 1/2 chicken; cover with 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat.	Top with 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes to hour.

title: golden tea bread
directions: Drain 3 tablespoons pineapple juice and save for topping. Combine pineapple, squash and vanilla.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil and beat.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture alternately with pineapple mixture. Beat after each addition.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Turn onto wire rack; spread with topping.
Mix 1/4 cup brown sugar (packed) with reserved pineapple juice.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup confectioners sugar. Blend until smooth.
Spread on loaves.

title: pheasant and wild rice
directions: Bring first 9 ingredients to a boil in sauce pan. Place bacon in cooking bag. Sprinkle rice and mushrooms over bacon. Add pheasant, Pour soup mixture into bag. Seal and slit according to directions.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: grilled turkey breast
directions: Cover turkey with marinade; let sit overnight.
Grill 12 minutes on each side.

title: fruit jiffy torte
directions: Beat first three ingredients until well blended.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Add flour and beat until fluffy. Pour 3/4 of batter into a well-greased rectangular pan (9 x 13-inch).
Spread on pie filling.
Make a lattice top with the remaining batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cake is cool.

title: refrigerator cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and confectioners sugar. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Set aside. Save about 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top.

title: ham hocks and black-eyed peas
directions: In a large flameproof casserole, combine all ingredients except ham hocks and heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Place ham hocks on top of mixture and reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until beans and ham hocks are tender.
Cooking time:
2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Lay ham slices out flat.
Cut cheese in half crosswise.
Place cheese on ham slice and also one asparagus spear.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Place on baking sheet and bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: squash bake
directions: Mix.
Add bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat, until well blended, for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, chopped candies and mint flavoring.
Spoon into crust and chill.

title: mostaccioli
directions: In oil, saute 1/2 cup each green pepper and onion.
Add the ground beef; cook until brown.
Stir in the diced tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Cook the noodles according to package directions.
Cut the Velveeta into thin slices.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownies
directions: Combine chocolate and butter. Cool. Sift flour once; measure. Add baking soda and salt; sift together 3 times. Beat sugar slowly into eggs and continue beating until light and thick. Add chocolate mixture. Blend well. Add vanilla and nutmeats. Add flour. Stir until smooth. Turn into greased, shallow pan (8 x 8-inch). Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. When cool, cut in squares and remove from pan. Makes 16 brownies.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shells.
Slice peaches on top of cream cheese mix.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add boiling water.
Bring mixture to a boil and let thicken.
Set in refrigerator; let cool, not set.
Put strawberries in pie shell and pour mixture over them.
Bake shell before putting in strawberries.
If big strawberries, cut in half.
Let cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: heather's easy apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples and bread.
Put bread in bottom of pan.
Put apples on top, then pour mixture over that. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Chop onion and fry with parsley (if fresh) in 1/2 cup olive oil.
Let cool.
In large bowl, mix zucchini, onion and parsley. Mix eggs, Bisquick, grated cheese, salt, pepper and Mozzarella. Mix well, then pour in greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Let cool and serve.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, onion and chestnuts.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Take out of oven.
Put buttered cracker crumbs on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy, then gradually add brown sugar.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Drop from a teaspoon.
Bake in a 275° to 300° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool on a rack.

title: make ahead s'mores
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat.
Stir in milk and vanilla; cook until smooth.
Make 1 s'more at a time. Spread 1 tablespoon of chocolate mixture on 2 whole graham crackers.
Place 5 to 6 mini marshmallows on one cracker.
Gently press the other cracker on top.
Repeat.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Store at room temperature.

title: homemade "milky way" ice cream
directions: Melt candy in milk.
Blend in eggs, sugar, Eagle Brand milk and whipping cream.
Pour into gallon container of freezer and add enough milk to finish out the gallon.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 400°, until set in the middle.
Casserole should be set in pan of water for cooking, but if pan is too large for this, place a pan of water directly under casserole while baking.

title: diet mexican pie
directions: Add hamburger meat to sauce.
Mix well.
Pour into small casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cooked grits and cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fettuccine with olive sauce
directions: In a saucepan, prepare fettuccine as label directs.
Drain. Return to pot and keep warm.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; do not peel.
Slice fairly thin.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Thinly slice onions and separate into rings. Cook bacon in skillet.
Add onions.
When bacon begins to sizzle, cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Into a greased casserole, put a layer of zucchini.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Dot with catsup; cover with onions and bacon.
Repeat.
Have a layer of onions and bacon on top.
Dot with catsup.
Cover casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp clemenceau
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and saute garlic 3 to 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and juice.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Mix sauteed potatoes into this mixture.
Add peas and parsley.
Heat thoroughly.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over brownie "crust."
Top with fruit and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza.
Chill until served.

title: turkey chili for weight watchers(low-fat)
directions: Brown turkey and sausage; drain excess liquid.
Combine cooked meat with rest of ingredients and simmer until flavors blend.
This is a very spicy chili!
If you prefer less spicy taste, use 1/2 can Ro-Tel and less of chili seasoning.

title: turtle bars
directions: Combine caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring until melted.
Combine remaining milk with cake mix and melted margarine.
Press half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread melted caramels over chips.
Mix nuts in remaining cake mix and drip spoonfuls over caramels.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck; add garlic salt.
Drain.
Cook lasagna noodles or large egg noodles.
Add tomato sauce to meat.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse boneless chicken breast.
Spray glass baking casserole dish with some nonstick cooking spray. Arrange chicken in baking dish; sprinkle on lemon-pepper seasoning.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond rusk(kavring)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and flavoring and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Beat.
Add almonds and divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Shape into 15-inch rolls (logs).

Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove rolls from pans and cut into 3/4-inch slices at an angle. To serve, place on a cookie pan; toast until light brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter on top of stove.
Turn stove down to warm and add the peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Place in unbuttered pan.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and egg until light.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture alternately with 1 cup milk.
Chill dough for several hours or overnight.

title: spicy chicken and rice
directions: Combine bouillon granules and water in an electric skillet; bring to a boil over high heat. Add rice and return to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Cut chicken into bite size pieces and add to skillet. Add tomatoes and next 9 ingredients. Stir well and cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Remove bay leaf. Add peas; toss gently. Yield: 6 servings.

title: spaghetti for 50
directions: Add oil to electric roaster.
Add meat.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add onions and all seasoning salts.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until onions are clear.
Add catsup, tomato juice, water and mushrooms. Cook 2 to 3 hours real slow.
Stir occasionally.
Add bay leaves and parsley.
Cook spaghetti according to package.
Cook 1/2 at a time.
Do not rinse.
Add to sauce.
When it starts to boil, turn roaster to 250°
for 2 hours.
Do not stir hard.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Sprinkle apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons butter.
Put into pie shell.
For topping, mix 1 cup flour, brown sugar and 1 stick oleo.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's favorite coffee bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Melt margarine over low heat in water and milk.
Allow to cool.
Add to flour-yeast mixture.
Add eggs, beaten and flavorings.
Mix in flour in several steps. Knead into a ball; cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rest.
Divide dough in half and roll or pat into a rectangle.
Sprinkle nuts and fruit, then roll up and place in loaf or panetone pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Brush top with egg wash or milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on lowest rack at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Loaf should sound hollow when tapped.
You can remove it from pan and bake a little longer on the rack if it doesn't sound right.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Mix cocoa and confectioners sugar.
Sift them, if necessary. Cream in softened margarine.
Blend in vanilla and evaporated milk until of spreading consistency.
Frost your favorite confection and enjoy.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Saute mushrooms, pepper and onions in a little butter and water.
Drain and add to removed pulp of baked potatoes, which has been mashed.
Add a little milk to potatoes.

title: bacon-cheddar muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups and top of pan or spray with nonstick spray coating.
Sprinkle pan with cornmeal, if desired.
Or line muffin pan with paper bake cups (but still grease tops of pans).
Set pan aside.
In bowl, stir together flour, cheese, sugar, baking powder, salt and red pepper.
Make a well in the center.
In a small bowl, combine egg, milk and oil.
Add egg mixture all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Fold in the crumbled bacon.
Fill prepared cups even with the top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins are golden.
Remove muffins from pan; serve warm.
Makes 8.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage lightly with salt.
Combine sugar, vinegar and salad dressing; pour over cabbage.

title: sofia's swedish strawberry cake(light sponge cake with fruit and whipped cream, delectable!)
directions: Using mixer, beat eggs and sugar until almost white and frothy.
By hand, fold in flour and baking powder.
Pour into prepared spring-form pan (greased and dusted with breadcrumbs). Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and then remove from pan. Split with breadknife into 2 layers.

title: orange banana salad
directions: Place orange slices in a bowl. Combine honey and cloves; pour over oranges. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Discard cloves. Arrange greens on salad plates. Top with orange and banana slices.
Drizzle with honey mixture. Sprinkle with coconut. Yield: 2 servings.

title: cocoa date cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar, eggs, flour and cocoa. Then add date mixture. Pour in greased pan. Sprinkle 1/2 c. sugar, chocolate chips and nutmeats on top. Bake 350 for 30 minutes.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Blend thoroughly in blender.

title: fettuccini with cheese and cream
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles.
Heat butter and cream over low heat until melted.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over hot noodles.
Stir until noodles are well coated.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Cut off top of cake about 1/2 to 1-inch deep.
Scoop out center and tear into pieces.
Dissolve Jell-O and add juice from berries. Chill until thick, but not set.
Fold in strawberries, angel cake and 1 cup whipped cream.
Gently place in scooped out cake.
Frost with whipped cream.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: cheese ball with beef
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 3/4 package of beef.
Shape into ball.
Chop up remaining chipped beef in small pieces and roll the cheese ball around in it.
This also may be frozen.

title: colorful veggies
directions: In skillet, cook garlic in oil.
Add celery, red pepper (or green) and oregano until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add beans and carrots.
Heat through.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls and press down with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: delectabites
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and vanilla until well blended. Gradually stir in flour, then walnuts.
Shape into crescents or 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in upper third of 350° oven for 10 minutes, until firm but not browned.
Gently roll each cookie in powdered sugar, cook on wire racks.
Drizzle cookies with melted chocolate.
Let stand on waxed paper until chocolate is firm.

title: nancy's cheese and spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish. Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: minced clam dip
directions: Blend cheeses together well.
Add clams and sauces.
Mix in enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat the pineapple to boiling.
Dissolve in the hot pineapple the cherry jello and lemon jello.
Add the pecans, celery and apples.
Add the Cokes.
Chill.

title: seaside clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Add carrots, celery, potatoes and seasonings.
Stir in flour.
Add clam juice.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add milk, corn and clams.
Heat slowly until hot. Serves 4.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup water and cornstarch to thin paste.
Combine 1 1/2 cups water and sugar in top of double boiler and bring to a boil over direct heat.
Add cornstarch paste and cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Return to double boiler and continue cooking until smooth (15 minutes).

title: quick ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze.
Add fruit, if you like.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onions, carrots and celery in margarine. Add chicken broth and simmer 30 minutes. Add potato soup, cheese, salt, pepper, Tabasco and sour cream. Simmer 15 minutes. Do not boil. Makes 10 cups.

title: daddy's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions, garlic and celery in melted butter or margarine until brown.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato strips with cheese
directions: Place potatoes in a greased baking dish; add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 425° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and parsley.
Cover and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate angel food cake
