directions: Combine flour packet from cake mix with cocoa.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions; then fold chocolate flavoring into batter.
Bake according to package directions.
Sprinkle cooled cake with powdered sugar.

title: my mom's chicken and noodles
directions: To Make Noodles: Mix eggs and flour together and roll out on a floured board. Roll thin and let noodles dry out (about 4 to 5 hours). Cut into bite size pieces. Cover chicken with water and use 1 large can of chicken broth. Boil chicken, celery, onions and salt. Cook until chicken is done. When chicken is cooled, debone and put back in broth. Use a large kettle. After the noodles are dry, cut up. When broth is hot, add noodles to broth and cook until they are done. If you want thicker broth, add a little water and flour mixed. Do not cover.

title: low-fat burritos
directions: Spray one side of each tortilla with Pam.
Stack tortillas on top of each other and wrap with plastic wrap.
Place tortillas in microwave approximately 1 minute on High.
Heat beans until warm. On the center of tortilla, spread beans, lettuce, tomato, salsa, onion and cheese in a line about 1/4-inch from one end. Fold side of tortilla, then end, then the other side.
Place in preheated oven at 345° for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix the biscuit mix with the grated Parmesan cheese.
Add a dash of pepper and the beaten eggs.
Fold in the zucchini.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Use 2 tablespoons of batter for each patty and fry the patties, 4 at a time, until golden brown.
Makes 12 patties.

title: pickle roll-ups
directions: Dry pickles on paper towels.
Spread cream cheese (softened with a little milk) around each pickle.
Hold pickle on fork to facilitate spreading.
Wrap beef slices (one or two per pickle) around each pickle.
A little cream cheese on edges of beef will make it stick together.
Chill in refrigerator for at least two hours, then slice in rounds.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients together in large mixing bowl. Add grated carrots last.
Makes three 8-inch layers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook onion with cube of margarine until onion is soft.
Add soup, sour cream, salt and cheese.
Mix together with cooked potatoes.
Put in baking dish.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine and add to crushed cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
May be microwaved for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: lentil stew
directions: Rinse and drain lentils.
In a large saucepan, combine lentils, chicken broth, undrained tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, parsley, basil, garlic and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 to 50 minutes, or until lentils and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let simmer on low for several hours in advance of serving time.
Continue simmering and serve hot on demand.

title: gracie's summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: ham-cheese squares
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into oiled 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs with a fork, stir in milk and oleo.
Combine the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add to the liquid mixture. Stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Add blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sesame seed salad
directions: Brown sesame seed to a dark brown color, but do not burn. Prepare Romano cheese in slivers or coarse grated (slivers are best).
Break lettuce by hand.
Combine lettuce, sesame seed and Romano cheese, mixing well.
Add dressing just before serving (Wish-Bone Italian seems to be the best for this salad).
Leftovers do not keep well.
Amount of sesame seed and Romano cheese can be varied to taste.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add Pet milk.
Cook on slow fire until boiling.
Check for soft ball stage.
After it forms a ball, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail; mix with pudding mix in microwave-safe dish.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently to prevent lumps.
Cool.
Mix canned fruits and fresh fruits (those listed or anything you like except strawberries).
Stir in pudding and refrigerate.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper, olives, red onion and parsley in a large bowl. Whisk oil, vinegar and oregano in a small bowl. Pour over vegetables. Toss to coat. Gently stir in cheese. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: mystery punch
directions: Place dry ice in punch bowl; pour on ingredients in order: pineapple juice, lemonade, ginger ale, sparkling water, limeade and strawberries.
Dry ice gives off smoke vapor.
When ice is exhausted, add more.
Serves 25.

title: tammy's world famous swedish meatballs
directions: Roll in small balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done (15 minutes).
Simmer meatballs in sauce.

title: chicken divan
directions: Debone and simmer the chicken breasts for 1 hour.
Add salt while cooking.
Butter a casserole dish.
Cook the broccoli (less time than directions).
Mix the soup with the mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Layer as follows:

title: philip's fried green tomatoes
directions: Roll
sliced tomatoes in flour.
In frying pan, put the vegetable
oil
and butter; place individual slices in pan and cook until tender.	Cook at medium heat.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: turkey soup
directions: Wash turkey breast.
Place in a large pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.
Remove from broth and cool.
Dice.
You may not need all of turkey meat.
Add to broth the bouillon cubes, carrots, celery and soup.
Add more water if needed to make more broth.
Cook until tender.
Add diced turkey and cooked rice a little at a time so as not to get it too thick.
You may not need all rice.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Add all ingredients to saucepan; add 1 quart of water.
Bring to a boil. Slowly drop in meatballs; lower heat to simmer and cover for 3 hours.
Serve on your favorite pasta.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onion until meat is brown. Drain.
Snip sauerkraut.
Mix with 2 tablespoons bread crumbs. Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic salt and pepper and stir into sauerkraut mixture.
Chill.

title: cherry crepes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend sour cream and brown sugar. Set aside.
Beat baking mix, egg and milk with rotary beater until smooth.
Spoon 2 tablespoons batter into hot lightly greased 6 or 7-inch skillet. Rotate pan until batter covers bottom. Bake until bubbles appear.
Gently loosen edge.
Turn and bake the other side.
Spoon 1 tablespoon sour cream mixture onto 1/2 of each crepe. Roll up.
Place crepes, seam side down, on ovenproof platter.
Bake about 5 minutes.

title: iced tea
directions: Bring to boil 6 cups of the water.
Add tea bags and turn off stove.
Let tea brew 25 minutes.
In 1 gallon container, mix sugar and lemon juice.
Add tea and mix.
Add remaining water.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Grease mold.
Soften cream cheese and boil tomato soup.
Mix in gelatin.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Finely chop shrimp and add to mixture.
Pour into mold and chill.
Yields approximately 4 cups.
(Fills Tupperware Gel and Serve mold.)
Serve with crackers or party breads.

title: grandma's  party mix
directions: Mix all cereal together in a large paper sack. Mix together nuts, margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasoning salt. Add to cereal and mix well. Spread on cookie sheets and heat in oven at low temperature for 40 minutes.

title: stars and stripes mold
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water into red gelatin in medium bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in half the cold water.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate for 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Spoon over marshmallows.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put food in a food processor and chop.
Then pour in bowl and chill.

title: brown sugar fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla together; blend well.
Serve warm or cold with fresh fruit.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, dry ingredients, nuts, chips and oatmeal.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
When cool, place in glass gallon jar.
Will stay crisp.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: vegetable roll
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in bowl and set aside.
Make Bisquick.
Roll out on floured board about 1/4-inch thick. Spread hamburger mixture and roll up like a cinnamon roll.
Cut into 2-inch lengths and put in pan with meat upright; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While baking make a cheese sauce.

title: woody's revenge
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large jar. Place ice in glasses and fill with mixture. Garnish with orange slices and cherries. Be careful of the second drink.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and garlic in
hot margarine until yellowish.
Add meat and brown.
Pour off any excess fat. Add vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Pour mixture into square baking dish (9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch).
Press olives into mixture.
Combine corn meal, milk and eggs.
Spoon over filling. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cherry cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling in bottom of pan.
Add pineapple (do not drain).
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple; pour butter on top of cake.
Mix coconut and nuts; sprinkle on top of butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli-tuna casserole(no fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain.
In large bowl mix together sour cream, Miracle Whip, cheese, milk and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add hot noodles, tuna, broccoli and green onion.
Stir and blend evenly.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Place
all
ingredients in a skillet or large saucepan. Cook over
medium
heat,
stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Cook until nuts are coated with sugar and it appears the water has cooked
out.
Spread
in a large, shallow pan and bake at 250° for about an hour.
Do not overcook!

title: butterscotch brownies(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend oil and sugar.
Stir in unbeaten egg.
Sift flour and baking powder together and combine.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: chicken rice-a-roni meat dish
directions: Place meat in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Brown Rice-A-Roni as described on box.
Pour over and around meat.
Mix flavor packet in water.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil and punch holes in top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party chocolate pie(yields one 9-inch pie)
directions: Requires no cooking!
Cream margarine with electric mixer, adding sugar gradually.
Add cooled chocolate, vanilla and extract.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: coffee crunch cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Let cool and cut into 4 layers.
Stack layers, spreading about 1 cup of Coffee Cream Frosting between each layer and remaining Coffee Cream Frosting and Coffee Crisp on top.
Chill until ready to serve, but not longer than 3 hours, or Crisp will begin to melt.

title: no-knead dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1 tablespoon water and 1 tablespoon sugar. Add butter (that is melted and cooled), sugar, salt, beaten eggs, warm water and flour.
Stir together well.
Let stand 1 hour. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight after brushing the top with melted butter.

title: crab au gratin
directions: In medium saucepan, saute celery and onion in butter.
Blend in flour, then add milk.
Add seasonings and remove from heat. Gradually add egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat and add crab meat, stirring carefully. Pour into greased casserole dish or baking pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and spices together and pour over cucumbers and onions in a gallon jar.
Set in refrigerator.
Eat anytime.
Very good.

title: puppy chow(lighter eating - 5 points)
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Then pour over box of Crispix cereal, Mix well. Then put powdered sugar in a bag and pour cereal mixture in the bag and shake well until coated well.

title: mexican hat dip
directions: Put refried beans on the bottom of Pyrex pie plate.
Add salsa to taste.
Put guacamole on top of the beans.
Spread sour cream in middle.
Cut medium ripe olives in two.
Put around sour cream in the middle.
Serve with tortilla chips/veggies.

title: rosanne's fruit dip
directions: Using an electric blender, mix together Marshmallow Fluff, cream cheese and milk.
Chill.
Serve as a dip for fresh fruit.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in greased dish.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Cover pineapple with flour mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over pineapple.
Mix crackers and cheese together.
Cover pineapple with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes until bubbly.
I use a little more cheese than this calls for and sometimes I use
Townhouse crackers instead of Ritz.
This is great with ham.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and soups together.
Top with onions.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine all three ingredients; beat at least 2 minutes until fluffy.
Pour into 8-inch graham cracker pie crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Spread fruit on top (canned pie filling or fresh fruit).
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: stir-fried broccoli and carrots
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli which has been cleaned, trimmed and cut into florets and slice stalks.
Cut carrots into matchstick strips and cut the onion into wedges.
Stir-fry for 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add water chestnuts that have been drained and sliced.
In a small mixing bowl, mix cornstarch and Karo syrup until smooth.
Stir in cider vinegar, soy sauce and ginger.
Add to skillet, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Sprinkle with cashews.
Serves 4.

title: german sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the pasta according to package directions, omitting the salt.
Drain.
Rinse under cold, running water to stop the cooking and drain again.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and add the soup and cheese.
Heat until the cheese melts.
Add broccoli and water chestnuts.
Simmer until the broccoli thaws.
Add the rice and pour into a buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: very rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl and form into balls. "Will be sticky."
Roll balls in either powdered sugar or Dutch cocoa. Refrigerate. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: olive garden alfredo sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in sauce pan.
Add 1 tbsp cornstarch or flour to thicken.

title: pull apart bacon bread
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain; crumble and set aside.
Place oil in skillet; heat over med. heat until warm, add pepper and onion, saute until they are tender.
Cut biscuits in fourths and place in large mixing bowl.
Add sauteed vegetables, crisp bacon, margarine and cheese; toss until thoroughly mixed.
Place in a 10 inch tube pan coated with a vegetable cooking spray. Bake 350° for 30 minutes, Immediately invert onto large serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cook peas according to package directions and drain.
Fry bacon until very crisp.
Wash and dry lettuce.
Put lettuce in large bowl torn into pieces.
Next, place the chopped bell pepper and onions, spreading them out over the lettuce.
Pour the cooked, drained green peas over the top, then put mayonnaise over the top of the peas, spreading it out and then sprinkle sugar over.
Put grated cheese on next, covering the top and then garnish with small pieces of the cooked bacon.
Refrigerate overnight before serving or at least 6 to 8 hours.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer until lightly fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to butter mixture, beating after each addition, until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into cake batter.
Bake in 3 waxed paper lined 9-inch pans in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat (but do not boil) to blend flavors.
Use as a basting sauce for meat or as a dipping sauce. Will taste best if refrigerated for a few days to blend flavors. Keep unused portion refrigerated.
Will keep for quite awhile.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop into lightly greased pan by tablespoonfuls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken delight
directions: Remove fat or gristle from chicken.
Split each piece into 2 thin layers, then cut layers into strips about 2-inches long, 1/4-inch wide.
Cook rice according to package directions (omit margarine).
Heat oil in skillet or wok, add chicken.
Stir constantly until chicken turns white and is slightly brown (approximately 2 minutes).
Turn heat to medium and add peppers, celery, onion, bouillon cube, water chestnuts, salt, ginger and water.
Make a smooth paste of arrowroot and soy sauce and stir in chicken mixture until smooth.
Cook gently 6 to 7 minutes, tightly covered.
Add bean sprouts to cooked vegetables; cover and cook gently another 2 minutes.
Each serving consists of 1/2 cup cooked rice with 1 cup chicken mixture.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and 1/4 tsp. cinnamon.
Mix well. Pour into a well greased casserole dish.
Combine the remaining 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon with the remaining ingredients for topping.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken latki's
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into cakes.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Serve with Corn Tomato Relish.

title: lobster newburg
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine. Stir in flour and salt. Add milk all at once. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more. Stir half of the hot mixture into the beaten egg.
Return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir mixture until thickened, but do not boil.
Stir in lobster, dry sherry, red pepper and white or black pepper.
Heat through.
Serve over English muffin halves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meal-in-a-dish
directions: Chop onion and green pepper until fine.
Brown onion, pepper and hamburger.
Let cool, then dip off grease.
Stir in 1 egg. Layer in baking dish as follows:
corn, meat mixture and tomatoes. Cover with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Salt to taste.
Dot small amount of butter on top, if desired.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: corn souffle casserole
directions: Dissolve flour in melted butter.
Add sugar and stir well. Slowly add evaporated milk.
Stir in eggs and baking powder.
Add corn; blend thoroughly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top of casserole with mixture of cinnamon and sugar when baking is complete.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries on paper towels.
Melt margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Cool if too soft.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in jar for use in other recipes.

title: tiramasu
directions: Beat egg yolks, 1 egg and sugar for 8 to 10 minutes until very firm.
Fold in grappa.
Add Tia Maria to sweetened Espresso.
Dip ladyfingers (1 or 2 at a time) very fast in hot Espresso mixture. In pan, make layers:
1/2 ladyfingers, 1/2 custard (marscapone mixture), 1/2 ladyfingers, 1/2 custard.
Right before serving, sprinkle with unsweetened cocoa.

title: lemonade refresher
directions: Pour lemonade concentrate into blender.
Add melon balls and blend at high speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into tall glasses and top with sparkling water.
Serves 4.

title: chicken chili casserole
directions: Mix chicken, jalapenos, soup and milk together real good, then stir in cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and shortening, then eggs, then nuts and lemon juice, then mashed bananas.

title: old-fashioned mush
directions: Bring water to boil.
Combine corn meal, sugar, salt and cold water.
Stir combined mixture into boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Pour into loaf pan and chill.
Take out of pan and slice it.

title: spinach party salad(great for a luncheon)
directions: Wash and drain spinach and lettuce well.
Spread spinach in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Add layer of eggs.
Scatter peas on top.
Spread onion rings over that.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream and spread over top (like frosting on cake).
Arrange Swiss cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Do not toss.
Add bacon over top before serving.
Cut portions in squares all the way through and serve to plate with spatula.
Tuna, shrimp, turkey, crab or lobster may be added. Serves 8 to 9.

title: fruit supreme
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Fold in fruit and nuts. Refrigerate at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: chef sauce a la "maple leaf"
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into quart size jar.
Shake thoroughly.
Chill.
Excellent served with white and purple cabbage slaw with diced celery.
Refrigerate remaining dressing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put last 4 ingredients in basket of percolator.

title: raspberry slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale and raspberries and freeze.
To serve, soften frozen mixture and pour in ginger ale and add mashed raspberries.
Serves 50.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onions and beef until browned.
Add salt and pepper. Add soup; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes; add milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
May be topped with cheese. Add cheese during last few minutes of baking.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onions, salt, sage, and pepper.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Combine brown sugar, catsup, nutmeg, and dry mustard; pour over loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Bake all ingredients at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cicatelli
directions: Pour flour into bowl.
Make a well.
Add remaining ingredients and knead well.
Roll out into strips the size of a pencil.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Press down with index finger.
Place in pan of boiling water with salt for about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and serve with your favorite sauce.

title: green chili
directions: Heat oil in large stockpot.
Add pork, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Saute until pork is browned.
Drain juice from tomatoes into stockpot.
Chop tomatoes and add to pork with chiles and 2 cups water.
Stir well and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and corn; mix with mayonnaise, soup, onion and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Pour in dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg and cream well. Add boiling water, then cold water.
Sift dry ingredients together and add all at once, beating well with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Can be made into cupcakes or small cake pans.
Batter is thin.

title: barbara's corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Combine oil, egg and milk together; mix well.
Stir into dry ingredients until just blended. Pour into well buttered 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
May be doubled; use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: play dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients in nonstick pan.
Add food coloring to water and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring continuously until thick.
Play dough is done when you can stick your finger in and it comes out clean.
Store in Ziploc bag in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cover bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with 5 cups diced rhubarb.
Spread 3 cups mini marshmallows over rhubarb.
Sprinkle with 3 ounce package of strawberry jello.
Next, prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Spread over mixture in pan. Sprinkle with the brown sugar.
Bake according to directions for cake.
Serve with whipped cream.
Best if eaten fresh.

title: chicken cacciatori
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Rinse chicken pieces, coat with the ingredients in the bag.
Heat oil in a skillet and brown chicken well on all sides.
Add garlic, onion, tomatoes, oregano and sherry.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: savory french bread
directions: Combine dry yeast and warm water; mix and set aside. Meanwhile, combine olive oil, basil, oregano and garlic powder in a saucepan; heat until warm. Combine flour and sugar; mix with yeast mixture and olive oil mixture. Stir well to create dough. Place on lightly floured surface and knead for several minutes. Allow to sit for 30 minutes to rise. Place on a greased baking sheet; brush with olive oil and bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: best baked bean casserole
directions: Mix all cans together in large oven container.
Do not drain. Add bacon, brown sugar, cider vinegar, onion and garlic salt. Bake uncovered at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: nanny's baruzzi (spaghetti soup)
directions: Cut up onion and with oil, saute in a medium size pot until onion is browned.
Remove onion.
(Leave onion in pot.)
Put in sauce and oregano.
Stir and cook on medium flame.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs until blended; beat 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients except carrots.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in carrots.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp #5
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in lightly buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve with warm milk or whipped topping.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in Pyrex dish and baste with sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Continue to baste and turn chicken midway.

title: empanadas
directions: Brown beef; add onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain excess oil.
Add cinnamon and raisins.
Set aside to cool.
In a mixing bowl, mix Bisquick and milk.
Form into a ball.
Roll out into floured surface and roll out into a thin rectangle.
Cut into squares.
Fill each square with a tablespoon of meat mixture and close to form a half moon, sealing in meat mixture tightly.
Fry these little half moons until brown.
Drain and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and place in bottom of casserole dish. Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream together. Pour over chicken. Melt margarine and mix with Ritz crackers. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes or microwave for 20-30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Use a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix flour, margarine and pecans and press into bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix with electric mixer, confectioners sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of flour mixture.

title: frozen daquiri
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and freeze.
To serve, top with more ginger ale.

title: parsleyed new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and peel a 1/2-inch strip of skin from around the center of each potato.
Drop potatoes into boiling salted water. Cover and reduce heat.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. While potatoes are cooking, melt butter in skillet.
When potatoes are done, drain and add them to butter.
Sprinkle parsley over potatoes and toss well to coat.

title: peanut patty
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water
and	bring
to
a boil for 1 minute, then add peanuts
and
food
coloring.
Boil
until
a small drop put into cold water forms a hard ball.
Remove from heat and add oleo and salt.
Beat until real thick and sticky. Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
When done, cut into small pieces.
Combine chicken, cream of mushroom and chicken soup, chilies and 1 can of milk in pan and cook until it comes to a boil.
Tear up tortillas and line bottom of oblong dish.
Pour soup mixture, then Cheddar cheese.
Repeat steps until soup mixture is used.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rainbow party punch
directions: In medium bowl dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water; set aside.
In large bowl, combine pineapple juice, ReaLemon lemon juice and gelatin mixtures.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour juice mixture into punch bowl; add sherbet and club soda.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together in crock-pot. Cook about 5 hours. Stir occasionally. May be put in casserole dish. Bake about 1 hour at 350°. Stir occasionally.

title: deer salami
directions: Mix well and form into 2 rolls; wrap in foil. Refrigerate 24 to 36 hours. Punch holes in bottom of foil and place on broiler pan. Bake 2 hours at 350°, depending on size of rolls. Or pork sausage, get pork and mix it with deer. Use 2 deer to 1 pork.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: devil's chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in a large bowl.
Marinate the chicken in the mixture for at least 2 hours.
Grill on a medium-hot charcoal barbecue (or electric grill) until the juices run clear.
Keep basting with the remaining marinade while grilling.

title: roast beef
directions: Punch holes in roast and put
a one-inch piece of onion, a garlic clove and a pepper in each hole, along with a little salt. Rub salt and red pepper all over the roast.
Put olive oil in roaster on top of stove.
When hot enough, sear all sides of roast in the olive oil.
Pour 3 cups of wine and a little water in roaster and add chopped onions.
Place covered roaster in 400° preheated oven.
Basting occasionally, cook 2 1/2 hours for roast with medium rare center, longer if well done meat is desired. Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs; drain macaroni and rinse well.
Add soup, milk and pepper to macaroni, mixing well.
Spoon in Cheez Whiz, mixing as well as possible without tearing up the macaroni.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove cover and microwave another 5 minutes, until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt.
Remove from heat and add butter and garlic cheese.
Beat eggs in measuring cup and fill with milk (1 cup).
Pour into grits.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: seven-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and cool slightly.
Add 7-Up and set slightly.
Add other ingredients and set until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil, sugar and eggs, beating after each egg.
Add carrots and pineapple, then add nuts. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes in 325° oven.
Pour icing over cake while still hot.

title: herb pretzels
directions: Stir together.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Stir and mix, then bake 15 minutes more.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Spread 3/4 of cheese and spinach in bottom of pie shell.
Beat cream, eggs and salt until frothy.
Pour over cheese and spinach. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pie has set.
Broccoli can be substituted for spinach.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients in order listed, mixing sour cream, Miracle Whip, sugar and milk together.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Toss and serve.

title: tarragon chicken breasts
directions: Heat oil in Dutch Oven with 1 Tbsp. butter.
Add chicken; saute, turning on all sides until brown.
Remove the chicken.
Add shallots and carrots to drippings; saute, stirring 5 minutes, or until golden.
Return chicken; heat.
When hot, slightly heat cognac in ladle and ignite.
Add white wine, chopped tarragon, chervil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, gently, covered, 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to heated serving platter; keep warm.
Strain drippings in Dutch Oven; return drippings to Dutch Oven, discard vegetables.
In small bowl, combine cream, egg yolk, flour; mix well with wire whisk.
Stir into drippings in Dutch Oven; bring just to boiling, stirring.
Add more wine if sauce seems too thick.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms in hot butter 5 minutes, until tender.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Garnish with tarragon and mushrooms.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hens slowly in a small amount of water until tender. Take meat off the bones and cut in bite size pieces.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon in 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes; cool.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers, top and sides.
Decorate with nuts (optional).

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in crock-pot; add wieners.
Simmer 2 to 4 hours.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions; set for 1 hour. Drain and rinse.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Mix, pour over and freeze.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls; spread flat in pizza pan.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread on baked crust. Top with chopped veggies and cheese.
Cut in squares.
Serve cold.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all in dish.
Top with crushed Town House crackers.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: turtle ice cream pie
directions: Crush wafers and add sugar and melted butter; press into pie dish.
Let ice cream soften, then press it into dish.
Drizzle caramel over top and sprinkle pecans over caramel.
Store in freezer until ready to serve.
Add whipped cream before serving.

title: yogurt dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar. Shake before using. Makes 1 cup, 20 calories per serving. Refrigerate.

title: gon lo mein
directions: Heat wok and add oil.
Stir-fry onion, celery and char siu for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add noodles, bean sprouts, green onion and sesame oil; cook for 3 minutes.
Combine soy sauce, oyster sauce and sugar.
Add to noodles.
Toss lightly to mix.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Mix beaten eggs with oil and juice from strawberries.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time. Mix well.
Fold in strawberries with juice remaining.
If you like, you may add berries from another box.
Do not add any liquid from 3rd box.
Pour into small pans (well-greased).
Use 4 to 5 pans or regular loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove from pans when cooled.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix oats in hot water and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix all other ingredients well, including melted butter.
Stir in oatmeal well, but do not use electric mixer.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Ice while hot.

title: beef rolls (for spaghetti sauce)(braciole di manzo)
directions: Cut the beef into 4 slices.
Season with salt and pepper. Combine the remaining ingredients, mix well and sprinkle over the beef slices.
Roll like a jelly roll and secure by winding white heavy string around the braciole.
(Remove string before serving.)
Brown the braciole before adding the tomatoes for the sauce.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add in layers the next 5 ingredients in order listed.
Do not stir.
Pour sweetened condensed milk on top without stirring or mixing.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and process 15 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiano
directions: Wash and cut eggplant.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Heat olive oil in frying pan.
Dip eggplant in egg and water mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Place eggplant in frying pan and brown slowly on both sides.
In a baking dish, put 1 cup tomato sauce, then a layer of fried eggplant, a little sauce, sprinkle some grated cheese.
Repeat with eggplant, sauce and grated cheese to make 3 layers.
On top sprinkle with grated cheese, sauce and Mozzarella slices.
Cover and bake 15 minutes more at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a baking dish. Cover with topping and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef casserole(serves 6)
directions: In a casserole dish, layer cabbage, onions and potatoes. Slice corned beef and place on top of vegetables.
Mix soups together and pour over corned beef.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot macaroni # 2
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Put into crock-pot.
Beat eggs and can of milk.
Stir in cheese; add regular milk.
Pour over macaroni.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake 3 hours on low.

title: grandma king's prune cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Pour in foil-lined pan (10 x 14-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Mix sugar, yeast, salt and water together.
Let sit 5 minutes. Add soft lard and flour.
Let raise.
Knead.
Let raise again. Roll out a little at a time.
Spread margarine.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in strips and twist.
Put in pan and let raise. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine the apples with the cinnamon and sugar, fixed to taste. Do not cook apples too mushy.

title: baked tomato beef balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour and soup.
Form into ten balls.
Roll in flour and brown in a little fat.
Place meatballs in a casserole.
Cover with soup, diluted with 1 cup hot water. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour and oleo together.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (like a pie crust).
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups and broth and pour into a casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll meat in flour and brown in oil.
Remove.
Add onion and brown slightly.
Return meat.
Add wine.
Cook slowly until most of the moisture is absorbed.
Add seasoning and consomme.
Simmer covered for about 15 minutes.
Add sour cream just before serving. Serve over rice.
You may add mushrooms during the last 15 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix chocolate, sugar and flour.
Add water; mix and then add milk.
Then cook over medium heat until it thickens.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Stir butterfingers into softened ice cream, then pour into pie crust and freeze.
Yield:
3 pies.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Mix sugar, nutmeg, ginger, eggs, shortening and flour.
Next, mix baking powder and baking soda with buttermilk and blend together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and then roll out; cut and fry.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Heat skillet; add bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir-fry about 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: beef burgundy for two
directions: Wrap steak with bacon; secure with string.
In medium skillet, melt butter and brown steaks 2 minutes on each side.
Add mushrooms and cook until mushrooms are tender.

title: seafood dip or spread
directions: Cut seafood into small pieces. Add softened cream cheese and other ingredients. Mix well and chill. Can be served with crackers, chips, or as sandwiches. This is a favorite sandwich I serve my bridge club. It isespecially good on cheese bread.

title: dutch baby
directions: Note:
Make at least 1 hour ahead or refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add the strawberry gelatin and a few drops of the red food coloring.
Mix in the strawberries.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: turtle pecan cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place cookies in resealable plastic bag. Squeeze out excess air; seal bag.
Roll over cookies with rolling pin until finely crushed.
Combine cookie crumbs and butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain and thaw spinach.
Chop scallion greens and water chestnuts.
Combine all the above ingredients at least one day before serving.
Serve with your favorite bread chunks or crackers.

title: lynn gray's chile dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in a skillet.
Drain the fat. Add the ketchup, chili powder, salt, mashed kidney beans and liquid and salsa.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, top with cheese and bake until melted in a 350° oven, 10 to 20 minutes.
Top with chopped green onions and sliced olives, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: winkler's moravian sugar cake
directions: In
a
half
cup
of warm water (110°) add 1/2 teaspoon sugar and sprinkle 2 packages of active dry yeast.
Set aside until yeast
bubbles.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed or with wooden spoon.
Add
an
additional 1 3/4 cup flour.
Place in greased bowl,
grease top of dough;
cover and let rise until double, about an hour.
Punch dough down in greased pan (17 x 12 x 1-inch deep).
Let rise 30 minutes.
Spread evenly in pan and
sprinkle evenly
with
brown
sugar	and cinnamon.
Make shallow indentations
with	fingers.
Dribble
with
stick melted and cooled butter.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Pour into large bowl.
Add nuts, mini marshmallows, coconut, half jar of cherries (halved), and sour cream and mix thoroughly.
For fun, smooth top of mixture and create a face with the remaining cherries.
Chill one hour.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 3 quarts.

title: pear-banana-lime mold
directions: Pour milk into freezer tray.
Freeze until edges are icy. Drain pers, reserving syrup.
Add water to make 1 cup; bring to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling liquid.
Chill until
partially set.
Gradually add milk to gelatin, whipping until double.
Dice pears.
Slice bananas; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Fold fruits into gelatin.
Pour the mixture into a 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Chill mixture until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Cook vegetables and herbs in chicken broth until soft.
Puree until smooth and add 1/4 cup sherry. Warm cream and stir in just before serving.

title: pressed chicken
directions: Grind chicken.
Add dressing, mayonnaise, red pepper, salt and lemon juice.
Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Bring remaining 1 1/2 cups chicken broth to boil and dissolve gelatin. Mix all ingredients and mold.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight. Toss before serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello, pineapple, cottage cheese, and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: mary jane's beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, saute beef in heated butter.
Add onion soup and beef broth.
Let come to easy boil, then turn down to medium. Stir flour into sour cream container.
Mix well, then add to skillet, stirring constantly.
It will become thickened, but creamy, not stiff.
Add cooked noodles.
Let simmer 15 minutes to 30 minutes.

title: roulades of sole florentine
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain well and chop.
Season with onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Rinse and dry sole.
Spread gray side with approximately 1 1/2 tablespoons spinach mixture.
Roll up and lay in casserole, loose end down.
Tuck any extra spinach around rolls.

title: beef taco bake
directions: Saute ground beef.
Place pieces or tortillas in baking dish. Add cooked ground beef. Add tomato sauce, water, salsa and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.

title: thai beef salad
directions: Place steak in large plastic bag.
Blend lite soy sauce, lime juice, brown sugar and garlic, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove 1/4 cup mixture; pour over steak.
Press air out of bag; tie top securely.
Turn over several times to coat both sides. Marinate 30 minutes, turning bag over occasionally.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut breasts up into pieces.
Mix flour, egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces into batter and fry until brown. Great cold or hot.

title: slush(an icy punch)
directions: Note:
Seven-quart container or combination pitchers (plastic) to equal approximately 7 quarts.

title: teriyaki potatoes(microwave dish)
directions: Wash potatoes and scrub with a vegetable brush.
Cut new potatoes into quarters.
Place in 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole dish.
Add butter, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning and peppers.
Toss to combine.
Cover, microwave cook on 100% power for 12 to 15 minutes, or until tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Garnish with snipped rosemary and serve with sour cream.

title: yellow dream cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and mix alternately with milk and vanilla to cake mixture.
Last fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 greased layer pans at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool, then frost with chocolate frosting.

title: upside-down german chocolate cheese cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions and pour into pan.
Mix melted oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over batter and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pecan smithfield chicken
directions: With knife, slice a pocket in thickest side of each chicken breast.
Fill each pocket with a slice of country ham and pecans which have been sauteed in butter.
Dip each chicken breast in flour.
Brush on beaten egg and dip into mixture of bread crumbs and pecans.
Cook chicken in pan of oil 3 or 4 minutes on each side, then place in baking dish and finish cooking in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: thin coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes at 350° for 30 minutes or until set and browned.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in ice cream maker.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Fill cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Place 1 heaping teaspoonful of egg mixture on top.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake one hour at 300° or until set and brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat until fluffy, sugar and oil.
Mix all together; add eggs and add apples.
Mix well.
Pour in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add ground apples, raisins, vanilla and soda mixture, stirring well. Sift dry ingredients together, add the nutmeats and combine with the first mixture stirring until well mixed.
If too stiff add a little water.
Pour into an oiled loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: grandma's borscht
directions: In a large soup pot, boil meats and 2 tablespoons salt in 1 gallon of water.
Skim top.
Add garlic, parsnip, carrots, leek and dill. Boil for another hour.
Remove meat to use for pirozhki or another meal. Add to the pot the cabbage, tomato paste and liquid from the can of beets.
Boil for 1 more hour.
Cut the beets and add just before serving.

title: ruby salad
directions: Add gelatin to boiling water and stir.
Add wine, rind and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add fruit.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: snappy wieners
directions: Score wieners diagonally.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In small mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour over wieners.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crispy pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers 1/4-inch or less thick.
Put into a large pot or crock; cover with solution made of 2 cups hydrated lime and 2 gallons water.
Soak 24 hours, stirring occasionally, then rinse well (use 3 waters at least).
Cover with clear, cold water and soak 3 hours.
Drain and pat dry on towel; cover with following mixture.
Let soak overnight in vinegar, sugar, spices and salt. Next a.m., boil 35 minutes and pack in sterile jars while hot and seal.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store dry.
Mix 2 tablespoons with 1 cup hot water.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add shortening.
Stir until melted. Add sugar and salt.
Mix in enough flour to handle.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Mash down.
Form into rolls.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: surprise salad
directions: Combine dry Jell-O, cottage cheese and Cool Whip, mixing well. Stir in pineapple and pour into serving dish.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and jell Jell-O, boiling water, crushed pineapple and pie filling.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream, then add sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Blend.
Spread on top of Jell-O.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple sandwich spread
directions: Cook on low heat until thick.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise into quarters.
Stand down in quart jars.
To each jar, add 1 teaspoon alum, 1 clove garlic, 1 hot pepper and 2 dill heads or 1 1/2 teaspoons dill seed.
In stainless steel pan, boil vinegar, water and salt for 5 minutes. Pour boiling liquid over cucumbers and seal.
Let stand at least 6 weeks before using.
Makes 8 to 10 quarts.

title: bruschetta(garlic toast)
directions: Toast the bread slices and while still hot, rub each well with the cut side of a garlic clove.
Drizzle a tablespoon of olive oil over each slice.
Add a little salt and plenty of pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process until smooth. Makes 1 1/4 cups or the equivalent of 1 can.

title: poor man's chop suey
directions: Saute onions, ground beef and celery.
Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Five minutes before end of baking time, place Chinese noodles on top.

title: microwave banana cream pie
directions: Place pudding in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook full power 6 to 8 minutes or until pudding boils and is thickened.
Stir 2 to 3 times while cooking.
Add marshmallows. Heat full power 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until marshmallows melt.
Stir halfway through heating time.
Cover with wax paper and chill.
Whip cream until stiff in small bowl.
Fold into cooled pudding.
Slice bananas into pie crust.
Pour filling over bananas.
Chill several hours before serving.
May top with whipped cream.

title: chicken cheesy rice pie
directions: Have cubed, cooked chicken and prebaked pie shells ready. Prepare the rice and peas by cooking according to package directions.
Add rice and peas to chicken in a large mixing bowl and lightly toss to blend.
Pour half the chicken mixture into each pie shell.
Pour 1/4 cup milk over each pie filling.
Pat and stretch biscuits to make top pie crust, using four biscuits over each pie.
Pinch edges to shell, crimping and pinch seams where biscuits meet each other.
(Biscuits stretch better at room temperature than straight from refrigerator.)
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Serve immediately with hot milk.

title: strawberry crunch cake
directions: Sift together sifted flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk and stir into flour mixture, blending well.

Spread evenly in greased 11 x 1 1/2 x 7-inch pan. Spoon strawberries over batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Mix butter, remaining sugar and flour and crumble over berries. Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Stir together salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serves 6.
Prep Time:
30 minutes plus chilling.

title: chocolate chunk pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla in medium bowl with a whisk. Stir in pecans. Sprinkle chocolate chips over bottom of crust. Pour pecan mixture into pie shell. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from center comes out with little bits of filling attached. If browning too quickly, cover with foil. Cool on wire rack for 2 hours. Refrigerate until serving time. Makes 8 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Cut bread into cubes.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Sprinkle with cheese and seasoning.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: tasty pumpkin cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in mixing bowl; beat well.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, ginger and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine over cake mix, stirring gently with fork into cake mix.
Do not mix into pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
Cut into servings.
Garnish each serving with whipped cream.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown crumb sausage in a heavy skillet; drain on a paper towel.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator overnight covered.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: all-star apple pie
directions: Combine pie filling, lemon jucie and cinnamon in a bowl. Mix well and spoon into pastry shell. In another bowl, combine flour and brown sugar; cut in butter until minture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in nuts, oats and coconut; sprinkle over pie filling. Bake at 400 degrees for 12-15 min. or until topping is golden brown. Cover edge of pastry with foil to keep from over browning if necessary. Cool on a wire rack before cutting.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all together.
Top with grated cheese and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
This makes a very large casserole.
It can be divided and put in several dishes and put in freezer for later.

title: grandma hardy's christmas cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder like pie crust.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Last, add Crisco.
Roll and cut in shapes. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and put all but last two ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan. Just before putting in oven, put the melted butter and cornflakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Dredge beef strips in mixture and set aside.
Heat the oil in a frying pan or wok. Brown the beef strips until tender.
Toss in the vegetables, cooking until tender, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with the water and add to beef and vegetable mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: crab puffs
directions: Cream all ingredients except crab meat and English muffins. Fold in crab meat. Split English muffins and spread mixture on top of English muffins. Then place on cookie sheet and put in freezer for approximately 15 minutes. Then cut each English muffin in 6 pieces. Then place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well and spread on large cookie sheet.
Brown hamburg; drain and cool.
Spread over mixture.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes and onions over top of hamburg. Top with Cheddar.
Eat with dip size corn chips.

title: baked cod-russia(zapechonaya treska)
directions: Soak Cod in water for one hour. Clean it, slice it into strips. Boil in water with pepper, carrot and onion for 15-20 minutes. Chop potatoes. Put fish into a stew pan as a first layer, add chopped potatoes and parsley. repeat layers. Whip sour cream with eggs, add salt. Cover Cod and potato mixture with sour cream sauce. Bake in oven at 375F for 20-30 minutes. Garnish with greens. Serves well with a vegetable salad.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans. Mix well. Press into 13X9 inch pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes. Cool completely. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 c. of the Cool Whip. Mix well. Spread over crust; chill. Combine puddings and milk. Beat 2 minutes with mixer. Spread over cream cheese layer. Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry-fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients
in
a
large pot.	Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars.
Water bathe for 10 minutes. (Place sealed jars in
pot,
cover with
water and boil for 10 minutes.)

title: gourmet chicken spaghetti(serves 12)
directions: For sauce:
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add half and half and 1 cup chicken broth.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, wine, garlic powder and cayenne pepper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes in large bowl.
Add celery.
Add onion, bacon and 6 sliced eggs.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Start oven heating at 375°.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Beat in sugar until very stiff.
Blend in vanilla and fold in chips.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet from a teaspoon.
Place in oven; turn off heat.
Do not remove cookies from oven until oven and cookies are cold.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Cover top with butter.
Top with crushed crackers. Bake 30 minutes at 250°.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown; add chopped onion.
Saute until tender; drain off grease.
Add soups, sour cream, pimento and seasonings. Mix well.
Fold in noodles.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Put buttered crumbs on top and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart bowl on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil; stir after 3 minutes. Mix well again, scraping bowl.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Drain pimientos well. Mix all ingredients well. Roll in a ball or log. Roll in pecans. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: mixed fruit
directions: Put undrained pineapple chunks, undrained peaches, undrained apricots and drained oranges in a large bowl.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit.
This will dissolve easily and turn into a sauce.
Mix lightly, but well, being careful not to break up fruit.

title: crab stew
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk slowly and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Season and add crabmeat.
Do not permit to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 ounces of sherry wine.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Roll into one-inch balls and chill.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip each ball in chocolate mixture, leaving small spot on the top not covered so that candy resembles buckeyes.
(Insert toothpick in candy to dip in chocolate.)

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in large Dutch oven on top of stove.

title: green and white salad
directions: Wash and cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Chop onion. Mix.
Make sauce of the next 4 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Add the Worcestershire sauce and mix together.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Mix dough ingredients and set aside for a few minutes.
Roll out, cut with round cookie cutter.
Place 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon of the date filling on it.
Cut a tiny slit on top of the top cookie and place it over the filling.
Press the edges of the two cookies together with your fingers.
Scrape the excess back into the cookie.

title: sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix mayo, sour cream or yogurt together.
Add 1/2 pkg. Hidden Valley Ranch Dressing mix.
Combine chicken, celery, grapes, nuts, and salt with dressing.
Chill.
For variation substitute craisins or dried cherries for grapes.

title: sweet sandwich spread
directions: Cook on low heat until thick sugar, egg, butter and lemon juice and rind.
Add raisins.
Cook a little more.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and mayonnaise.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir in water.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture. Stir in raisins.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: garden pea casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Saute pepper, onions and celery.
Add peas, water chestnuts, soup and milk.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan. Put bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: creamy cubed steak
directions: Cut steak into 4 serving pieces if necessary.
Combine cracked pepper and flour.
Dredge meat in mixture.
Discard any excess flour.
Brown steaks in 1 tablespoon butter over medium-high heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn steaks once.
Keep warm on serving platter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add remaining butter to skillet. Add sliced
mushrooms.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring, until golden.
Stir in sour cream, pepper, Worcestershire and paprika.
Heat, but do not boil or mixture may separate.
Spoon sauce over steaks and serve.
Sprinkle with more paprika if desired.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onion just until tender.
Pour into large bowl.
Add undiluted soup, oleo and cornbread mix.
Add 1/2 soup can of water.
Stir all together.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Eggplant may be used in place of squash.
Very good.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and whites separately, then together.
Add sugar, flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Lastly add hot milk with small piece of butter melted in.
(Use lemon flavoring.) Bake at 350°.

title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Mix tomato juice, olive oil, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
To this add diced cucumbers, onion, green pepper, tomato and carrots.
(Add any amount you desire, but not too thick.)

title: eggplant stew
directions: Cook onions, green peppers and ground beef in oil until meat is browned and vegetables tender.
Cut eggplant into 3/4-inch cubes.
Add eggplant, tomato and spaghetti sauce mix to meat mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until eggplant is done.
Top with cheese.
Cover and simmer until cheese melts.
What's left over, put in pita bread or flour tortillas and heat.

title: no cook chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients well and press into a greased pan.
Chill well before cutting into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken into bite-size pieces.
Place evenly in bottom of baking dish.
In small bowl, mix soup and sour cream together and pour evenly over chicken.
Mix melted butter and crushed crackers together with poppy seed.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until desired brownness.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add other ingredients.
Knead on floured board.
Separate into 15 to 18 balls and roll out.
Shape and place on pan sprayed with Pam.
Brush with Egg Beaters or egg yolks; sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes 15 to 18 pretzels.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine juices; add ginger ale just before serving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix stuffing, melted butter and onion.
Set aside.
Dilute soup with water.

title: banana split cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/2 cup butter or margarine in a bowl.
Mix well and spread and pat in bottom of an 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch shallow baking pan.

title: deluxe bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast bread slices lightly.
Trim crusts. Spread slices with margarine.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each slice into 4 pieces.
Arrange, sugared side up, in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Blend eggs, granulated sugar, vanilla and salt.
Slowly stir in milk. Pour over bread.
Place casserole in square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch. Pour very hot water 1-inch deep into square pan.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 65 to 70 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: guilt free cheese sauce
directions: Place margarine in a 1-quart glass bowl; microwave at High 30 seconds.
Stir in flour with a wire whisk; gradually add milk, whisking until smooth.
Microwave at High 6 minutes, stirring at 2-minute intervals until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese and next 3 ingredients, stirring until cheese melts.
Serve over steamed vegetables.
Yields 1 cup, 10 calories and 0.4 g fat per tablespoon.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Into hot pudding, stir
1/2 cup peanut butter.
Into baked pie shell, sprinkle 3/4 cup ground peanuts.
Pour pudding (cooled) over nuts.
Add all other ground nuts.
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Put on pie and bake just until lightly browned on top.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon in bowl and mix well.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat peaches, nutmeg and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon in saucepan.
Spoon over batter.
Bake at 350°
until golden brown.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Steam fry potatoes until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Saute onion and celery.
Add to other ingredients in a large stock pot. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: tarheel hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat heated to 375° (preferably that used for frying fish).
Hush puppies will rise to top and may be turned once for even browning.
When golden brown, remove to paper towel to drain excess fat.

title: asparagus with dumplings
directions: Do not drain asparagus.
Gently mix flour, eggs, baking powder and salt.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot water that asparagus has been cooked in.
Boil until tender, soft and fluffy, about 5 minutes.

title: lobster stew
directions: Saute lobster meat in butter for 2 minutes. Add tomalley and blend well.
Slowly stir in hot milk and cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat a little longer until piping hot, but do not boil. Serve with toasted crackers or toast points.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Line dish with Doritos. Spread chicken over Doritos.
Spread onion and green pepper over chicken.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes (I don't drain mine, I mash my tomatoes up).
Pour cream of chicken or mushroom soup over dish and spread.
Add Cheddar cheese soup and spread.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook hamburger with onion; drain.
Put in casserole; pour soup over meat.
Smooth over this.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Cook in oven until bubbly.
Add cheese on top, if desired.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Beat egg; add milk and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to milk mixture.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add liquid mixture to flour; stir well.
Turn on lightly floured cloth and knead for a few minutes.
Roll out about 3/8 inch thick.
Cut with large biscuit cutter.
Brush tops with butter.
Fold in half and press together lightly.
Place on greased baking sheet; line apart. Cover and let rise until double before baking.
Brush tops with melted butter again.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: delicious and easy brisket
directions: Line your turkey pan with aluminum foil to make a "t" in the center of the pan.
(Use enough foil to extend each end beyond the rim of the pan so you can seal the edges together later.)
Place the brisket fat side up inside the foil.
Sprinkle the package of onion soup mix on top of the brisket.
Do not add anything else. Tightly seal the foil, leaving a little air space between the brisket and the sealed foil.
Place the lid on the roaster.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour with pastry blender and mix all dry ingredients in together.
Beat egg until frothy and add to milk and water.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix with a fork.
Pinch into balls and roll one crust at a time.

title: cherry cheese cake tart
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and Philly cream cheese.
Place 24 cupcake papers on a cookie sheet.
Place vanilla wafers in bottom of cups.
Fill 3/4 full of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until it starts to thicken).
Remove from oven and top with cherry pie filling.

title: dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Cook noodles, drain and place in bottom of casserole dish. Brown beef and onions.
Add tomato sauce, catsup and water.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Spread mixture over noodles.
Mix mushroom soup, cream cheese and sour cream and spread over beef mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 350° or enough to heat thoroughly.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add vanilla.
Mix in powdered sugar.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients. In a large mixing bowl, break eggs over chopped apples. Stir lightly. Add sugar, vanilla, nuts and oil. Stir well. Add dry ingredients to this mixture gradually. Pour in a large, greased baking pan. Bake over 1 hour until done in a 325° oven. Raisins could be added. Use a 9 x 13 pan.

title: crockery barbecued beef
directions: For cooking liquid, in a bowl combine cola, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, garlic, bouillon granules, mustard, chili powder and red pepper.
Reserve 1/2 cup cooking liquid for sauce.
Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut meat to fit in crock-pot.
Pour remaining cooking liquid over meat.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 hours on low heat.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt the margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over butter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: all day beef stew
directions: Mix soup, water and flour; combine remaining ingredients. Cover pan and bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix above ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in baking dish covered loosely with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Melt butter in roasting pan; add lemon juice.
Arrange chicken pieces in single layer; turn to coat.
Sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Cover with foil.
May be prepared up to a day ahead to this point.
Bake at 250° for one hour and 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more at 400° until golden brown.
Thicken gravy; serve with brown rice.

title: spice rosemary cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and honey.
Add egg; mix well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well and add to first mixture along with water, to form soft dough. Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups of water to jello.
Add cranberry.
When cool, add apples which have been cut in small pieces.

title: waffles
directions: Separate
eggs.
Beat
whites
until stiff.
Set aside. Beat yolks.
Add
sugar
and
beat.
Add
sour cream, to which baking soda has been added.
Add flour, to which salt has been added as well
as
vanilla or cardamon.
Mix in melted butter and finally egg whites.
Make in waffle iron.
Serve cold with jelly or jam. Delicious.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and bell pepper in large bowl.
In small saucepan, bring to a boil cooking oil, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over raw cabbage, etc.
Stir well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Keeps for a long time and is better the longer you have it.

title: vegetable stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Place on baking sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Meanwhile, cook frozen vegetables according to directions.
Halve each potato; scoop out contents. Mash until smooth with the milk and butter.
Add salt and pepper. Next, spoon cooked vegetables into potato shells.
Place mashed potatoes on top of vegetables.
Return to oven (400°) and bake 15 minutes more or until golden brown.

title: best ever browning sauce and marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and chop in blender.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.
Wonderful painted on steaks, chops, hamburgers and roasts before cooking.

title: no fat italian dressing
directions: Combine and chill for 2 hours.
Remove garlic before serving. Makes 12 tablespoons.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown in skillet gd. beef, onions with oil.
Drain and add seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add chili powder, corn meal and water.
Simmer for 1 1 1/2 hours.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt milk and chocolate chips in double boiler.
In big bowl, mix marshmallows, peanuts and raisins.
Add chocolate.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool for 4 hours.
Makes between 70 to 80 pieces.

title: "dump cake"(for the lazy houseperson)
directions: In a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, put crushed pineapple and juice. Add pie cherries.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix; spread almonds or walnuts and dot with 1 cube butter or margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well; roll in nuts.
Form into balls or logs.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine the corn meal, paprika, black pepper, garlic powder and salt. Dip the chicken in milk. Coat in combined dry ingredients. Place chicken on 15 x 10-inch shallow baking dish; lightly brush with melted margarine (or spray with butter-flavored Pam). Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with fork.

title: donna's kartoffelglase (potato dumplings)
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Peel potatoes while warm and rice with a ricer.
Place riced potatoes in a large bowl.
Cut up bread into cubes.
Brown bread in margarine using low heat.
Put the bread around the riced potatoes in the bowl.
Sprinkle with parsley and salt.
When potatoes are cool, form a hole in the center and add the eggs.
Mix.
Add flour until dough is moist and does not crumble.
Form dough into 1 1/2-inch diameter balls. Drop into boiling water.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until they float. Serve with sauerbraten and gravy.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian beef in crockpot
directions: Place meat, bouillon cubes, garlic, and Italian dressing in crockpot.
Just cover with water.
Cook on low for at least 8 hours. Mix cornstarch in water and mix in crockpot to slightly thicken broth.
Shred meat with fork.
Serve over toasted French bread.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Simmer until all ingredients are thoroughly cooked and slightly thickened.
Good in filled cookies as well as pies.

title: key lime pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in a small bowl. Combine lime juice and egg yolks in a small, heavy saucepan; cook over medium-low heat until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes), stirring constantly (do not boil). Add gelatin to lime juice mixture; cook 1 minute, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat. Place pan in a large ice-filled bowl for 3 minutes or until mixture comes to room temperature, stirring constantly (do not allow gelatin mixture to set).

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix the dry ingredients:
cake mix, pudding and poppy seed. Add the eggs, oil and yogurt and mix well with a mixer.
Add nuts and fold in by hand.
Pour the mixture into a greased Bundt or tube pan; bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When cool, sift powdered sugar on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Break eggs in dish with melted butter.
Beat slightly and add sugar, then mix flour with sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and buttermilk, mixing well.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Tastes like egg custard without all the eggs.

title: sock-it-to-me cake with topping
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
