Pour 1/2 of mixture into a greased and floured tube pan.

title: toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
If using frozen pie shell, only use deep dish style and thaw completely.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; beat eggs well.
Add vanilla and fruit to egg mix, then add to flour and sugar.
Pour into 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool; cover with whipped topping.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Salt and pepper.
Add sweet basil, garlic powder and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.
Lightly grease baking dish.
Layer, starting with meat sauce, then lasagne noodles and mixed cheese.
Then add cottage cheese and layer of noodles and top with rest of meat sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to cool.

title: coushe-coushe
directions: Heat oil in black Dutch oven.
Mix cornmeal, salt and water until well mixed and pour into heated oil.
Cover and cook on high heat for about 5 minutes until a crust begins to form.
Stir very well.
Lower heat to medium-high, keeping covered.
Stir often, breaking up and mashing lumps.
Cook for about 15 minutes more. This makes lumpy coushe-coushe.
If you prefer it finer, continue cooking and stirring until lumps break up.
Soak for 15 minutes in milk before eating.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer in order.
Peas must be frozen.
Use the amount of ingredients according to the number of people served.
Make the day before, or allow at least 3 hours before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: monkey bread(easy - easy)
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip biscuits in mixture and put in layers in Bundt pan.
In pot, melt margarine and brown sugar; bring to a boil (about 1 minute), then pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Leave in pan 10 minutes, then turn over into plate.
Pull pieces off with hands and enjoy!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Flour and quickly brown chops in hot oil.
While browning chops, wash and peel potatoes.
Cut into thin slices.
Place potato slices in bottom of 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Peel and chop onion, placing it on top of potatoes.
Salt and pepper. Pour celery soup on top and spread over casserole.
Remove bones from chops and place on top.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze made of powdered sugar, lemon juice and butter.

title: cracker cake
directions: Add to beaten egg whites the cream of tartar and sugar.
Beat until glossy, not stiff.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla. Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Add as much Cool Whip on top as you want. Carefully add cherries or fruit filling on top.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour, water and crushed nuts together.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: banana nut cake(bread)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; beat well.
Add mashed bananas and egg yolks.
Beat.
Sift flour and baking powder together; set aside.
Mix baking soda with 1/2 cup of hot water.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the flour 1/2 at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in gently the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put in two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a 3-quart saucepan. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.

When syrup boils, blend in butter; stir frequently after mixture reaches syrup stage (230°). Add nuts when syrup reaches soft crack stage (280°); stir constantly until temperature reaches hard crack (305°).
Remove from heat; quickly stir in soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour on a cookie sheet. Spread evenly.
Let stand until cold and break into pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: decadent chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour well.
In saucepan mix melted chocolate and egg yolks.
Add milk and margarine.
Cook over low heat until combined.
Add sugar and flour.
Cook until thick and smooth over low heat.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill.
Decorate with sliced strawberries.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Grate cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and onion.
Place rolls in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spread the sausage over crescents, then spread on cheese.
Pour the egg mixture over this, then bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash or zucchini fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 1 can of corn, drained.
Put enough oil in skillet to cover bottom.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil; brown each side.
(If too thin and falls apart when done, add a little more Bisquick.)

title: s'more cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Stir together flour, graham cracker crumbs, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture, beating until blended.
Press 1/2 dough into pan.
Place chocolate bars over dough.
Break to fit. Spread marshmallow cream on top.
Scatter remaining dough over marshmallows; press to form layer.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool in pan before cutting into bars.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and flour or cornstarch and salt; gradually stir in milk and add chocolate squares.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks and immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooled 9-inch pastry shell.
Top hot filling with meringue and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy elegant stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound out chicken breasts. Prepare stuffing mix and place in center of each breast. Roll up and place in pan. Pour lemon juice over breasts and sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: lindy's strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add 7-Up.
Cook until thickened. Cool.
Add few (3 to 4) drops food coloring.
Slice berries or leave whole (your preference) and add to filling, then pour into pie shell.
Pie is best if you mix just before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Measure flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, baking soda, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, salt, buttermilk, oil, eggs and vanilla into large mixing bowl. Beat 3 minutes. Pour into prepared loaf pan. Smooth top. Combine 2 tablespoons white sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and butter, mixing until crumbly. Sprinkle topping over smoothed batter. Using knife, cut in a light swirling motion to give a marbled effect. Bake for about 50 minutes. Test with toothpick. When inserted, it should come out clean. Remove bread from pan to rack to cool.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt, in a separate bowl. Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Divide into 3 portions.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until easy to handle (about 1 hour).
Roll each portion 1/4 inch thick between waxed paper.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In medium soup pot melt butter.
Saute chopped leek and onion; stir occasionally.
Stir in pumpkin, chicken broth, salt, spices and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and puree mixture (may be frozen at this point).
Return to pot and add half and half and cook over medium heat.
Serve.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook together onions and potatoes in water until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Heat and serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until white in the middle (about 15 minutes).
Then cut into pieces and mix with the cream of chicken soup, sour cream and 1 teaspoon of poppy seed (in casserole dish).
Crumble Ritz crackers on top and pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle poppy seed over the top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit mold
directions: Dissolve 6 ounce package gelatin in hot water.
Add one 8 ounce can mashed, jellied cranberry sauce; stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in diced apples and oranges.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill 3 hours. Serves 10.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole dish. Heat in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: fiesta breakfast scramble
directions: In medium frying pan, cook sausage until done, drain and set aside.
While cooking sausage, chop peppers and onions and dice tomatoes, set aside in bowl.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper, parsley and garlic and pour into preheated nonstick frying pan on medium-low heat.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Add cooked sausage and chopped vegetables and cook until eggs are done the way you like.
Garnish with grapes and or strawberries and serve with whole grain toast. Serves 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine powdered milk, water, yeast, sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter and 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Add 2 cups flour, more if needed, salt, baking powder and soda.
Divide in 2 pieces and roll to 10 x 18-inch rectangle.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, broth, water, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in soups and milk and simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: deviled crab dressing
directions: In large, deep skillet over medium heat, melt 6 tablespoons butter.
Add scallions and celery.
Saute about 1 minute.
Stir in crab meat and saute briefly.
Stir in seasonings and bread stuffing.
Moisten mixture with half and half to taste.
Toss lightly.
Place dressing in lightly buttered baking dish.
Dot with any remaining butter.
Bake loosely covered with foil in oven with hens during last 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Next, combine eggs, 2 cups sugar, lemon juice and beat well. Sift together 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Sift into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes more.
Dust with confectioners sugar and cut into squares.

title: dirty rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package instructions and set aside. In large skillet, brown ground beef and ground sausage.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery; continue to brown until onion and bell pepper become transparent.
Drain meat mixture. Mix meat mixture into rice in a large dish and add green onion/parsley.
Stir all ingredients thoroughly and serve warm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll small balls in sugar. Place on cookie sheet, flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot dip
directions: Blend in food processor or blender the onion, tomatoes, cumin, m. s. g., garlic and peppers.
Leave chunky.
Heat to boiling, cool, then add Wesson oil.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks; add sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and rice.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: malt pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then flavoring to flour.
Add cocoa and salt.
Add the flour mixture gradually, alternately with milk.
Pour batter into tube cake pan (which has been greased and dusted with flour).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nana's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together and add salt, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine dry mix with egg mixture.
Add walnuts.
Divide into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: coconut-date balls
directions: Combine
dates	and margarine in skillet. Cook over low heat until
margarine
melts.
Add eggs and sugar. Cook, stirring constantly,
for
minutes or until mixture pulls away from side of pan.
Mix in Rice Krispies and pecans. Cool. Roll into marble size balls. Roll in coconut.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Season chicken and put a small amount of butter in a saucepan and brown chicken. Add water; cover and steam. After steamed, chop chicken and set aside. Cook rice. After rice is cooked, combine rice with broccoli (be sure it is thawed completely). Add 2 jars of Cheez Whiz, crabmeat, shrimp and soup. Add chicken and mix very well. Put in casserole dish with a cover. Cook in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: a most delicious pecan pie
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet until light brown.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating separately.
Add Karo syrup and pecans; pour in an unbaked crust and bake in moderate oven about 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown and firm.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice thinly the cucumbers.
Slice thin the onions and put in bottom of jar.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric and mustard seed.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Keep in refrigerator. Ready in 5 to 6 days.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix water and sugar; bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix or blend artichokes, mayonnaise and sour cream. Add 1/4 cup cheese and mix.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is light golden brown. Serve with your favorite crackers or vegetables.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Put mushrooms in clean jar; mushrooms should almost fill jar. Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over mushrooms to fill jar.
Marinate 24 hours minimum.
Serve cold.
Preparation time:
20 minutes. Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in flour, salts, milk and cream cheese.
Cook and stir until smooth and bubbly.
Put 1 cup of mixture into beaten egg; stir and then return to skillet.
Cook and stir until thick (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in broccoli.
Put 1 crust in pie plate.
Add meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Top with pastry.
Seal and flute.
Brush with milk.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter cup
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar, margarine, egg, peanut butter and vanilla until creamy.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Roll into 36 balls.
Place in mini-cupcake tins.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When they come out of oven, put mini-peanut butter cup in each muffin tin.
Cool completely.
Take out of tins.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: smores
directions: Break the graham cracker in two.
Also the chocolate bar in two.
Take marshmallow, put on top of graham cracker, then 1/2 of chocolate bar and the other 1/2 of graham cracker. Put in microwave for 30 seconds or until melted.
Then eat!

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients using only 1 cup of pecans in the mixture.
Roll the ball in the other cup of pecans.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in water until tender; drain.
Beat well and add all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Place a small amount of sauce on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place 1 layer of noodles in pan.
Combine cottage cheese and egg whites.
Place on top of noodle layer, then add sauce.
Place another layer of noodles; top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 (259 calories, 24.8 grams protein, 7.2 grams fat, 53 mg cholesterol and 332 mg sodium).

title: ortega chili casserole
directions: Beat cream, eggs and flour.
Split open chilis and remove seed.
Drain on paper towel.
Make layers of chili, cheese and egg mixture.
Pour tomato sauce on top and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, covered.
Enjoy.

title: fudge fancies(cookies)
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars together.
Add melted chocolate chips and eggs. Beat well. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Stir in and beat until well blended. Add vanilla and nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 3-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 11 minutes.

title: crock-pot bear
directions: Mix salt, pepper, onion and garlic powder. Roll roast in seasonings and rub them in.
Put roast in pot.
Heat water and dissolve bouillon cubes. Stir in Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, mustard and bay leaves.
Pour over roast. Add onions, pepper, potatoes and mushrooms.
Turn crock-pot to low and cook for 8 to 9 hours. Turn to high and cook for an additional 1 hour. Have plenty of biscuits for the gravy.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: beef and vegetable soup
directions: Boil meat in 2 quarts of water for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add vegetables.
Simmer for another 1/2 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Next, spread undrained crushed pineapple in pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Spread with coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: grape-nuts loaf
directions: Mix and bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll in egg roll wrappers, sealing end with a small amount of beaten egg.
Deep fry on high heat until brown.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Rub with garlic and thyme.
Brown in hot oil in nonstick skillet.
Combine 2 tablespoons of water with cornstarch.
Combine honey and mustard; stir into skillet.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir cornstarch mixture into pan.
Add 4 tablespoons of butter.
Cook, stirring until sauce boils and thickens.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms by brushing with crumpled paper towel or napkin.
Remove stems, dice and saute in butter.
Add seasonings, bread crumbs and spinach which has been chopped fine.
Add Cheddar cheese and cook until cheese is about to melt.
Take off stove, fill mushroom caps with filling and broil in oven for 6 to 8 minutes on second rack from top until fully bubbles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together (cream well).
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moist.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onion and cheese in a casserole dish.
Pour soup over them and repeat layers.
Add pats of margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Bone chicken and cut int bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients except tortillas and save some cheese for top.
Put in baking dish in layers with tortillas.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 9 x 2 baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes then cool.

title: breakfast cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and shortening.
Make into crumbs.
Set aside 2 large handfuls.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar and the 2 large tablespoons of Crisco for top crumbs.
Beat eggs; add milk and mix lightly.
Do not beat.
Put into two pans; top with crumbs and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 375° until done.

title: cheddar-scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt spread in small saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour and cook about 30 seconds.
Gradually whisk in milk until no lumps remain.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 minute, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pimientos, salt and pepper.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix well.
Roll into log and roll in chili powder.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill, slice and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: potatoes with sage and parmesan cheese
directions: Rinse potatoes.
Cut each into 6 to 8 lengthwise wedges.
Drop into boiling salted water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
(They should still be firm.)
Drain.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix and cream together all ingredients.
Put in ovenproof serving bowl.
Bake 15 minutes in a 375° oven (until bubbly). Serve with your favorite crackers or veggies.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bacon; drain.
In slow cooker, combine meat and remaining ingredients.
Cook slow for 6 hours. Stir often. Serves 12.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in large frying pan; drain fat, add celery and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add all remaining ingredients, except green peppers.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes. Add green peppers and cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef; saute onion and celery in pan as beef cooks. Season with salt and pepper.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine remaining ingredients; add beef mixture.
Stir in half of the grated cheese.
Top with remaining cheese and the crushed corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly and top brown.

title: italian salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine broccoli florets, cauliflower florets, sliced mushrooms and noodles in a bowl.
Pour dressing over mixture.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: lower fat chocolate pie
directions: Puree tofu in blender until completely smooth.
Melt chocolate over double boiler or in microwave.
Mix the chocolate into the pureed tofu thoroughly.
Add vanilla to the chocolate tofu mixture.
Place mixture into graham cracker crust and chill in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: baked apples(microwave)
directions: Wash and core apples; place in a 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) baking dish or four individual custard cups or shallow coffee cups. Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1/2 tablespoon butter in center of each apple.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes or until apples are just about tender.
Let stand several minutes.
Serves 4.

title: ham-n-egg pie
directions: Layer ham, eggs and biscuits in two layers.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: texas torte
directions: Combine eggs, flour, salt and milk; mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish that has been greased with Wesson oil or Pam. Do not use Crisco. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit, nut and lemon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add lemon flavor, then dry ingredients.
Mix together with chopped fruit and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add flour and eggs, then beat.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade sandwich spread
directions: Boil 10 minutes.
Make a thin paste, using 1/2 cup flour and water.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cook for 8 minutes more. Remove from heat; add 1 quart salad dressing.
Blend well.
Put into jars and seal.
Yield:
8 to 9 pints.
Serve with meats, salads or sandwiches.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and melt in a double boiler.
Serve in a fondue pot (or warming tray).
Dip with chunks of French bread or dipping chips.
Serves 12.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crumble Oreos in blender until fine.
Leave in separate bowl.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add to hash brown potatoes and mix.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: angel food heath bar dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with 1/2-inch slices of cake.
Mix pudding with the 1 3/4 cups milk.
Stir in softened ice cream.
Pour over cake. Frost with Cool Whip.
Crush the Heath bars and sprinkle over the top.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Then roll into ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: creamed potatoes(in white sauce)
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into pieces same size.
Put in saucepan. Add water to top of pan.
Do not cover.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste and 6 tablespoons margarine or butter.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Have all ingredients ready when guests arrive.
When the first guest arrives, give them the cheese and a grater.
Let them shred the cheese.
This is to achieve a sense of involvement.
Rub the inside of a large saucepan with the clove of garlic.
Discard garlic.
Pour the wine into the pan and heat it on medium.
Using your hands, mix the cornstarch or flour into the shredded cheese. When tiny bubbles form in the wine, add the pepper, salt and cheese slowly.
Stir constantly over medium to low heat until all cheese is melted.
Pour the melted mixture into 2 fondue pots or crock-pots and keep heated just short of boiling.
Add 1/2 of the liquor to each pot and stir.
Sprinkle the nutmeg over the top. To eat, dip crusty French bread pieces into the hot cheese mixture.

title: granola bars
directions: Place nuts, apples and apricots in a food processor; chop until fine.
Transfer to large bowl and add oatmeal.
In saucepan, combine butter, honey, sugar and cinnamon; bring to boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir into oatmeal mixture; add vanilla and salt. Press into a greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll.
Refrigerate, then cut into bar size.

title: sophie's pound cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except egg whites, in bowl, mixing until well blended.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour
into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven, then turn on to 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together
until moist; pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Arrange peach slices over crust.

title: squash relish(9 pints)
directions: Boil ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add squash mixture and boil 8 minutes.
Fill pint jars or smaller.

title: spoon bread tamale bake
directions: Time: 30 to 40 minutes.
Temperature: 375°.

title: vegetables with horseradish sauce
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook cauliflower and carrots, covered, for five minutes.
Add broccoli and cook all until tender.
Drain.

title: raw egg and rice
directions: Mix 3 or 4 cups of rice with 1 raw egg.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across grain into bite-size strips.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together the sour cream, flour and tomato paste.
Stir in the water, bouillon and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook fettucine.
Omit oil and salt.

title: grandma's lemon pie
directions: Mix and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet to make a crust and bake until golden brown.
Cool.

title: salad festival dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve over salad greens, topped with bananas, fresh pineapple, citrus, grapes and strawberries.
Add sliced celery, onion and green and red peppers. Sprinkle liberally with salad toppings and croutons.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 1 stick melted butter with crumbs and 1 cup confectioners sugar; mix well and press firmly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining stick of butter, sugar, egg whites and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Spread over crumb shell. Add a layer of banana slices and crushed pineapple.
Spread whipped topping evenly over fruit.
Sprinkle with pecans and chopped maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate until set (overnight). Yields 12 servings.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar together well, then add eggs and mix well. Add milk and mix well.
Cook until thick while stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.

title: cinnamon christmas ornaments
directions: Combine spices, blending well.
Stir in applesauce; mix well. (Mixture will be stiff.)
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness on an ungreased surface.
Using small or medium size cookie cutters, cut dough into desired shapes (i.e.
gingerbread men, stars, etc.) Peel away excess dough and re-roll.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in a saucepan with water, 2 tablespoons butter and a dash of salt.
Bring to a quick boil.
Cover saucepan and allow rice to simmer 15 minutes or until rice has absorbed all the moisture.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot until desired consistency.

title: crab meat cheese puffs
directions: Whip first 4 ingredients together.
Spread mixture on muffins and freeze.
A must.
To serve, put under broiler until brown and bubbly.
Do not burn.
Serve hot.
Can freeze for several days. This goes over big.

title: cowboy breakfast
directions: Saute potatoes in small amount of oil until tender.
Add onions, reserving some of green tops for garnish.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add eggs and scramble all together.
Season to taste.

title: stove top mac-n-cheese
directions: In large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta to al dente and drain. Return to pot and melt in butter. Toss to coat. Whisk together eggs, milk, hot sauce, salt, pepper and mustard. Stir into pasta and add cheese. Over low heat, continue to stir for 3 minutes or until creamy.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon, eggs and crackers; form patties.
Salt and pepper and fry in pan.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats and let stand while you mix cake. Combine the sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix all ingredients well, then add the oats and beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Good with no frosting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine oats, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugar until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely on wire rack or foil. Store in tightly covered container.

title: apple slices
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Make dough like pie; line a cookie sheet (using half of the dough).
Slice the apples. Combine with the cinnamon, butter, sugar and water. Cook about 5 minutes. Add the cornstarch and cook until thickened.
Pour over dough and cover with rest of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
While still hot, pour over powdered sugar icing, if desired.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Crush pineapple, using lid to press it dry.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; add pineapple, 1/2 cup nuts and rest of ingredients. Form into a ball.
Place remaining pecans on waxed paper.
Roll cheese balls in pecans, work pecans all around the ball.
(May take a little more pecans.)
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: h sauce(for horseradish haters)
directions: Melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in flour; then milk to make a smooth sauce.
Add mustard and heat until warm.
Serve warm with beef fondue or roast beef. Delicious cold on ham sandwiches.

title: party smokies
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except sausages and heat; mix well.
Add sausages and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with cocktail toothpicks.

title: walnut crown coffee cake
directions: Combine walnuts and sugar in a bowl.
Butter a 2 1/2-quart Kugelhupf or Bundt pan well and coat it with the walnut and sugar mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt).
Mix egg, buttermilk, butter and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat in flour mixture until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan and bake in moderate oven (350°) for one hour or until a cake tester comes out clean.
The cake may fall slightly.

title: bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick margarine. Mix other ingredients well. Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°. Top with 1 can French fried onions and bake just to crisp onions.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Pour into a large greased pan.

title: turkey chili
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the oil in a medium-size saucepan until tender, about 2 minutes.
Add the turkey and cook, stirring, until all signs of pink have disappeared and meat starts to brown slightly.
Add the tomatoes with their juice, chili powder, flour, cumin, ginger, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in the beans and reheat.

title: rick's colonel sanders chicken
directions: Fry 1/4 pound Heritage butter in a frying pan along with the chicken.
Fry until browned.
Combine all ingredients, except for chicken.
Place in large Ziploc bag.
Take the chicken and combine with the rest of the ingredients and shake as if it were Shake 'n Bake.
Bake chicken in oven at 350° until juices run clear.

title: bacon bars
directions: Stir cheese and bacon into dry mix.
Prepare dough according to package directions for rich biscuits, substituting bacon drippings for salad oil.
Knead as directed for rolled biscuits. Roll out to a 10 x 6-inch rectangle.
Cut into six 10-inch strips, 1-inch wide.
Cut each into thirds crosswise to make 18 bars. Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yields 18 bars.

title: hershey's fudge
directions: In large saucepan, dissolve sugar and milk, bring to a boil and boil exactly six minutes.
Stir and watch to prevent scorching. (Never boil less than six minutes.
A minute more won't hurt.) Have ready in a large bowl the chocolate chips, butter and vanilla flavoring (cut sticks of butter in small pieces).
Pour mixture over chocolate chips, butter and vanilla and beat until smooth and creamy.
(The more beating, the better the fudge.)
Add pecans, if desired.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Cool before slicing.

title: onion meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into 12 balls and arrange in a circle on a 10-inch microwaveproof pie plate.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back 2 inches at one side to vent.
Microwave at High 9 to 13 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Place pecan halves in unbaked pastry shell; set aside.
Combine semi-sweet chocolate and butter in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate and butter melt, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add corn syrup, sugar, vanilla, salt and beaten eggs to chocolate mixture, mixing well.
Pour mixture over pecans in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Serve pie warm or let cool completely on wire rack.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Saute the onions, mushrooms and green pepper in the butter until soft.
Combine the wild rice, shrimp, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce.
Prepare the cream sauce and add the sour cream at the end.
Combine all the ingredients.
Bake in a casserole in a slow oven, 300°, until very hot.

title: one dish company meal
directions: Grease large casserole dish with margarine.
Spread meat over bottom of dish.
Add water.
Arrange onion rings to cover meat. Scatter cubed potato over meat and onion.
Add carrot strips and diced celery and pour soup over all ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, apricot nectar and lemon Jell-O.
Add cake mix; beat until smooth.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan; bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake squares
directions: Mix apples, oil, sugar, eggs, pecans, cinnamon, flour and salt. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Spread 1 stick butter over hot cake. Mix confectioners sugar with milk so it is of spreading consistency. Spread over cooled cake.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Place oil into wok; add chicken meat and brown well.
Add celery, onion and seasonings; cook until everything is well done. Cook pasta in separate saucepan; drain and add to chicken mixture. May need to add 3 or 4 tablespoons of butter; mix and serve.

title: berry or peach baked dumpling
directions: Cream together the first 6 ingredients and pour into an ungreased 11 x 8-inch pan.
Add uncooked fruit and sugar for fruit.
Pour boiling water over top of the fruit.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: thai eggplant and shrimp salad
directions: Slice eggplant lengthwise; brush with oil.
Add garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until soft and lightly charred; let cool.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: 20-minute bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon over low heat until crisp, turning occasionally.
Remove from skillet and drain.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook and stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Crumble bacon; return to skillet.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: old-time syrup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Gradually add flour.
Pour in long greased and floured pan, about 10 x 14-inches.
Dough will be thin.
Some people do not like this cake overcooked.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Chill dough until firm enough to shape into 1 inch balls (at least 30 minutes).
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart and bake 10 to 14 minutes at 375°.
Cool 2 minutes and remove from pan while still warm.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar with a wire whisk.
Add onion and stir well.
Add oil, stirring constantly.
Add poppy seed and beat for a few minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook on low heat. Stir until it makes a ball.
Knead while warm.
Store in Ziploc bag.

title: northern california oyster stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Divide bread cubes between two large baking sheets and bake until dry (about 15 minutes).
Transfer to a bowl and add spinach.

title: caramel topping
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and cook for 20 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; beat until smooth. Pour over warm cake.

title: rice and hamburg casserole
directions: Brown Hamburg, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour covered; then uncover and cook for 1/2 hour more.
Top with Chinese Noodles or Onion Rings and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: moon cake
directions: Heat water and margarine to boiling.
Stir in flour until thick and smooth and pulls away from pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, using mixer.
Mix until shiny.
Spread mixture onto well-greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
If rises too high, prick with fork.
Let cool completely.
Mix pudding with 3 1/2 cup milk and cream cheese. Spread on crust, then spread Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: orange-glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In small bowl, mix with fork until smooth.
Makes 1/2 cup glaze.

title: pudding in cookie flowers(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 360°.
Prepare cookies.
Cream together margarine, sugar, Sweet 'N Low and vanilla.
Add flour alternately with egg whites mixing well after each addition.
Measure 1 heaping tablespoonful dough for each cookie.
Place 3 inches apart on a nonstick cookie sheet pressing batter with back of spoon in circular motion to extend circle to 4 inches.
Six cookies will fit on each pan.
Have muffin pan available to shape cookies after baking.
Bake cookies 8 to 10 minutes or until golden around edges.
Remove cookies immediately with a spatula and gently form into the muffin tin with hands, giving the cookie a cup shape. Return to oven and cook 5 minutes more.
Allow cookie shells to cool.
Remove from pan and store in a tightly covered tin.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cornstarch and sugar and beat again.
Add milk and finally the corn.
Mix well and pour into a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Place dish inside a larger pan filled with water. Bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes or until set (top is golden and a knife comes out clean).
Allow to set before serving.

title: angel sauce with angel cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Add juices.
Cook until thick. Add oranges and oleo. Serve over angel food cake. Use whipped cream on cake and then use sauce. Refrigerate.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage, then add remaining ingredients. Mix all together.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 325°, then top with 1/2 pound grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Can be put in a slow cooker or electric frypan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper, drain off fat.
In casserole dish layer bottom with meat mixture and then layer of sliced potatoes, meat mixture, potatoes.
Repeat until gone. dilute soup with 1/2 can water, pour over top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: bacon, cheese and onion canape
directions: Grind bacon, cheese and onion with medium grinder attachment, using equal parts.
Mix well and spread on rye slices.
Place under broiler until mixture melts and becomes slightly brown.
A favorite among guests.
Recipe is often requested.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cook to hard ball stage.
Pour over 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat until stiff enough to roll out on board.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Spread peanut butter to cover.
Roll and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Chill in refrigerator before cutting.

title: uncle ed desefanis' italian bread
directions: Combine yeast, sugar and 1/2 cup water.
In separate large bowl, mix 5 cups flour, salt, oil and remaining water.
When yeast is foamy, add to flour mix and beat vigorously until dough pulls from sides.
Turn dough onto floured board, clean and oil bowl. Knead dough 10 minutes adding flour if needed.
Return to oiled bowl, rolling to be sure dough is all covered with oil.
Cover and let rise at room temperature until triple in size (3 to 4 hours). Punch down and knead for 5 minutes and let rise again for 2 hours. Preheat oven to 400°.
Punch down dough; divide into fourths and shape into loaves.
Put on cornmeal dusted baking sheet.
Slash tops with sharp razor blade.
Mist spray water on loaves.
Bake 5 minutes later spray, 5 minutes spray again, bake until brown.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and peanut butter; add vanilla and egg, beating until fluffy.
Stir in soda and salt.
Blend in flour; mix until a stiff dough forms.
Best way to do this is with your hands; shape into walnut size balls and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork crisscross to flatten. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: lobster rolls
directions: In medium bowl, combine celery, mayonnaise, basil, lemon juice, black pepper, salt and red pepper sauce.
Fold in lobster until combined.
Cover and refrigerate at least 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned molasses cake
directions: If you use 3 eggs, then it takes 3 1/2 cups flour.
I usually make it without eggs.
That makes for a heavy cake (real good).

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: brunch
directions: Layer bread, sausage
and
cheese
in a 9 x 11 x 2-inch dish. Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour this mixture over the bread, sausage
and cheese.
Then pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup over that.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: jello dessert salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add water to make 2 1/2 cups. Bring to boil.
Add to jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Add mayonnaise.
Cool 5 more minutes.
Mix mayonnaise real well.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to thicken, then add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Put in oblong 13 x 9-inch pan or loaf pan.

title: lemon pepper pinwheels
directions: Marinade:
Combine all ingredients but meat and veggies.

title: dressing(for chicken or turkey)
directions: *Use chicken bouillon cubes if not rich enough.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: pan coating
directions: Blend until smooth, then put in jar or closed container and use
as
needed.
Heavily
coat
pan
before pouring cake batter into
them.
Coat using a pastry brush or folded paper towel or hands.
Instead
of
greasing and flouring cake pans, coat with this mixture.
Works great!

title: apple puffed pancake
directions: Melt butter with apples in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat in oven until butter sizzles.
Don't brown.
Remove from oven.
Mix the eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon until blended.
It should be slightly lumpy.
Pour batter on top of apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes until puffed and brown.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Trim and cut green beans into 2-inch sections.
In a nonstick skillet, heat margarine over medium-high heat.
Add green beans and saute 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly so beans cook evenly.
Add oregano and pepper.
Sprinkle with almonds and serve immediately.

title: perfect vegetables
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice the potatoes.
Dice onions.
Slice tomatoes and slice pepper in long strips.

title: old fashioned brown bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into 3 well-greased, one pound cans.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream mixture, except for nuts.
Add the nuts.
Add all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.

title: leek and bacon chowder
directions: Combine leeks, onion and bacon in large saucepan and saute in butter for about 5 to 6 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Stir to combine, then add flour.
Gradually stir in broth until smooth.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add cream or milk and cook until potatoes and leeks are soft.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chop suey(chow mein)
directions: Brown meats.
Add soy sauce and water.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Add cut up celery and onion.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
(Add some water if necessary.)
Blend cornstarch and water and stir into meat mixture.
(It is already rather thick.)
Add chestnuts, bean sprouts, drained mushrooms and heat through.
Season.
Serve over chow mein noodles or cooked rice.
Can be made a day early and refrigerated.

title: instant chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, pour off drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until golden brown.
Pour off drippings.
Add all ingredients to hamburger and let simmer about 30 minutes.
Very good with saltine crackers if thinned down or leave thick (no water) for hot dogs.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix until mixture resembles crumbs. Stir in cheese and buttermilk until dough leaves sides of bowl.
(Dough is sticky.) Turn out on floured board.
Knead about 10 times. Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut.
Place on ungreased baking pan. Bake until brown, about 10 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with 3/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Mix the other 3/4 cup sugar with cocoa, flour and salt.
Add enough hot water to dissolve mixture (very little).
Put the two mixtures together and mix thoroughly.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pastry shell and bake until firm, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375°.
Cool and cover with usual meringue.
Brown lightly at 350°.

title: cabbage burger bake
directions: Shred cabbage and spread 1/2 in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Saute bacon until fat starts to cook out, drain.
Stir onion and rice in drippings in pan, stirring constantly until onions are soft and rice is browned.
Spoon over cabbage.
Brown meat in same pan, spoon over rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and top with cabbage.
Heat sauce with water to boiling.
Pour over cabbage stirring lightly with fork so sauce flows to bottom.
Top with bacon.
Cover.
Bake 400° for 50 to 60 minutes until rice and cabbage is tender.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes to crisp bacon.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Place all ingredients in a large Ziploc plastic bag and shake well.
Remove as much air from the bag as possible.
Let chicken marinate for 2 to 3 hours in the refrigerator.
Remove chicken and grill.
Serve on bed of rice.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Place cake in a large bowl. Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Pour mixture over top of cake, letting some run down sides of cake and into bottom of bowl. Cover and refrigerate until mixture is set.
Invert
cake onto plate and slice.
Top with whipped cream.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift the next 5 ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Add the hot water and apples last.
Bake in greased round pie plate at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: the best sugar cookie you ever ate or snitched
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add next 4 ingredients.
After measuring flour, sift together with remaining dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dough will be soft. Roll balls in sugar.
Then flatten with palm of hand and mark with a fork or decorative cookie marker.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: deep fried onion flowers
directions: Peel onions, then cut a small slice off the top.
Starting at the top of onion and on one side, make a cut downward toward the bottom end of the onion.
Stop 1/2-inch from bottom of onion. Make additional cuts 1/8-inch from the first until they are completely across the onion.
Turn the onion a quarter turn so the slices are horizontal to you and repeat the 1/8-inch cuts until you have a checkerboard pattern across the onion.

title: pink lassies
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, cover and process on "stir" until smooth.
Delicious!!!

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Lightly brown okra and onion in the fat.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture is thick, about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Season with pepper and more salt, if needed.

title: stir-fry venison
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and saute for about 30 minutes, until meat is tender.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pasta shell vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese, in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes or until vegetables and pasta are tender.
Sprinkle soup with Parmesan cheese and serve.
Serves 4.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in deep bread tin.
Put bacon on top.
Bake in a hot oven for one-half hour at 400°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour. Bake at 325° in greased and floured or sprayed tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked fish(low fat)
directions: Brush fillet with melted butter and roll in bread crumbs. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn and bake for 15 minutes more.
Serve with lemon.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler until rice is done.
Beat eggs until fluffy; add vanilla.
Melt oleo in baking pan; let brown and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour rice in milk egg mixture and pour into square baking pan.
Pour about 1/4 cup white Karo over all.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean; cut in square and serve warm.

title: peach salad
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Mix until well blended. Spoon gently into bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy cheese and vegetable omelet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet with sloped sides, melt 1 tablespoon margarine over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add mushrooms; cook 2 minutes, until tender.
Remove vegetables from skillet. Drain on paper towels.
In bowl, mix egg with fork until blended. Stir in cream cheese, water, salt and pepper. Heat skillet over high; add remaining margarine and melt.
Pour in egg mixture. When eggs are set, add cheese.
Remove from heat; spoon vegetables over cheese.
Fold and serve.

title: connie's lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch prebaked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf sugar free
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover with sugar free yogurt.
Serve chilled.

title: old fashioned hermits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, spices and salt. Cream the shortening, sugars and eggs together.
Blend in flour mixture. Add raisins and walnuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain hearts and mash.
Mix all but last 2 ingredients. Place in quart casserole dish that has been greased.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: cheese-burger beans
directions: Scramble-fry ground beef and drain.
Mix beans, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Then combine with ground beef.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and bake for additional 5 minutes for cheese to melt. Serve with cornbread.

title: nutty cheese ball
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in 1 cup of chopped nuts into the mixture.
Shape into a ball and place in a covered container.
Refrigerate.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours to blend flavors.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in saucepan; cook over medium heat about 6 minutes until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Cool until thick enough to spread, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 2 cups or enough to frost top of 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: barszcz czsty wigllijny(clear beet soup)
directions: Soak mushrooms in water for 2 hours, then cook in same water until tender and set aside.
Peel and coarsely grate or thinly slice beets.
Cover with 4 cups court bouillon, including vegetables.
Add apples and cook until beets are tender.
Add mushroom water, 1 cup or more beet sour to taste, garlic, salt and pepper, red wine (optional) and sugar to taste.
Strain and serve. May be served with mushroom dumplings (Uszka).
Christmas Eve soup.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine raisin bran, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
(Will keep 5 to 6 weeks.)
Spoon batter into a greased muffin pan, 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: low calorie marinated chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken and put in bowl. Cover chicken with Italian dressing.
Marinate at least 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator. (Can be left in refrigerator for
3 days, no longer.)
Spray nonstick frying pan with vegetable spray.
Cook on medium until brown on both sides.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Defrost potatoes and mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in
9 x
13-inch	dish.
Top
with 2 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/2 stick oleo.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Mix all other ingredients and add onion and peppers.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
You may need to add a little water; stir.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Stir once after 30 minutes.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Drain. Stir in taco seasoning and liquid from ro-tel. Simmer. Add ro-tel. Mix spaghetti noodles and hamburger meat over low heat and top with cheese. After cheese melts, it is ready to serve.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, soda and salt, mixing well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and bacon drippings; stir until smooth.
Stir in cracklings.
Place a well-greased 9-inch square baking pan in a 450° oven for 3 minutes, or until hot.
Remove pan from oven. Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown on top.

title: noodle dinner
directions: Boil macaroni.
Add salt.
In skillet, brown hamburger and salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion.
When browned, add tomatoes with a little juice.
Simmer.
Add noodles; mix.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use as a substitute for 1 egg. Recipe may be doubled over and over depending on quantity of eggs needed.
Yolks may be boiled in water, shredded and used for other persons who are not on restricted cholesterol diets.
Egg yolks may also be frozen in water (covered) for use in other areas.

title: hamburger-barley-vegetable chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients, except barley.
Bring to a low boil, then reduce to simmer about 45 minutes.
Bring to boil.
Add barley.
Reduce heat.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: potatoes hashed in cream
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter, then stir in flour gradually.
Add cream and cook, stirring constantly, until cream bubbles and sauce has thickened.
Add salt, pepper, onion and nutmeg.
Mix well. Add the potatoes to mixture and mix well.
Pat into lightly greased 1 quart baking dish.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fresh haddock with shrimp sauce(serves 2)
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter and cook haddock.
While haddock is simmering, combine orange juice, Worcestershire sauce and sherry in medium bowl.
Add shrimp and marinate.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Serve with Russian rye or Hawaiian bread.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix well the ground beef, rice, onion, milk, salt and pepper. Drop by tablespoonfuls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine soup and water.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 round cake pans.
Cool.
Cut layers into two to make 4 layers using thread.
Combine sour cream, sugar and coconut; set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Layer with cake mixture ending with cake on top.
Take 1 cup of reserved mixture and blend with large Dream Whip.
Ice cake and put in refrigerator.

title: banana pudding delight
directions: Combine pudding mix and cold milk in mixer bowl; beat for 3 minutes.
Add condensed milk; mix well.
Stir in whipped topping and bananas.
Fold in vanilla wafers.
Pour into serving bowl. Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Makes 15 servings.

title: make-ahead butter-horns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add 4 cups flour, milk, shortening, sugar, eggs and salt; beat for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead lightly.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm room or until doubled, about 2-3 hours.
Knead dough down; dividing it into four equal parts.
Roll each into a 9 inch circle, brush with butter.
Cut each circle into eight pie-shaped wedges; roll up each wedge from wide to tip of dough and pinch to seal.
Place rolls, tip down, on baking sheets; freeze.
When frozen, place in freezer bags and keep frozen until needed.
To bake, place on greased baking sheets; thaw 5 hours or until doubled in size.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients
and pour over meatballs.
Simmer until ready to serve over rice.

title: banana salad
directions: Beat eggs well. Cook on low heat with sugar and vinegar. Stir this mixture real good.
(You can add sugar or vinegar to taste.)
When it starts to thicken, remove pan from burner.
After custard has cooled, add sliced bananas and crushed nuts. Chill in refrigerator.

title: german beef rouladen
directions: Cut beef into strips about 8 x 4-inch.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; spread with mustard.
In small bowl, mix onion, pickles and bacon.
Place some of mixture in each beef strip; roll up tightly and secure with string or skewers.
Brown rolls in a little oil.
Add water; simmer for 2 hours.
Make gravy by blending cornstarch and water, then stir into boiling liquid. Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles and green beans.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Sprinkle eggs with salt and pepper; beat in milk.
Layer 1 cup cheese and all sausage, crumbled.
Pour in milk and egg mixture.
Top with other cup of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until fork inserted in center comes out clean. Rub butter on crust edges before baking and lay foil loosely over top for any extended baking time.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook meat in large, heavy frying pan until it loses red color, but is not brown; drain fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes; stir as needed.

title: sauce for chuck roast(crockery cooking)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in onions and flour.
Stir until browned and add 1 1/2 cup meat broth and horseradish.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Serve with or on roast vegetables.
Serve with potatoes if you wish.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut off stems and remove seeds.
Thoroughly mix remaining ingredients and fill peppers.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 8 minutes on stove.
In microwave-safe bowl, mix all ingredients.
Then add cooked broccoli.
Microwave 10 to 15 minutes or can be cooked in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until top is bubbly.

title: chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil. Cover and cook until juices run clear, about 20 minutes. Remove chicken and keep warm. In the same skillet, saut mushrooms and onions until tender. Stir in wine or broth, butter, salt and pepper. In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water until smooth; add to skillet. Bring to boil and cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Return chicken to skillet and heat through.

title: hot chili(texas style)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Set the bacon aside and brown the chorizo sausage in the same pan.
Drain the sausage, reserving 2 tablespoons of the drippings and add to the bacon; set aside.
Add the sirloin beef, garlic, green pepper and onions to the reserved drippings and brown.
Transfer to large saucepan. Add bacon, sausage and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil; simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes about 1/2 gallon.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per directions.
Pour half of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes or until cake is done.

title: hash brown dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tourtiere(french canadian holiday meat pie)
directions: When onion is soft, add ground meat and cook until all pink or red is gone from the meat; don't overcook meat, it will be too dry.
Add salt, pepper and either allspice or nutmeg and cinnamon to your taste.
Put this filling in a pie plate lined with pastry. Cover with top crust and bake 35 minutes in a 425° oven until nicely browned.
Serve with steak sauce.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients. Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir together soda and salt. Blend into batter. Stir in nuts. Use 1 teaspoon of batter and form into small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 36 cookies.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Work together the first 3 ingredients.
Blend, then mix in the remaining ingredients.
Leave in refrigerator 1 hour before rolling out.
This is the key to this recipe!

title: carrot cheddar casserole
directions: Cook carrots, covered with small amount of salted water. Cook until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter and mash coarsely with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: my own easy chicken bake
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch dish or pan with foil, leaving enough on top to fold and seal.
Place chicken in dish and spoon celery soup evenly over chicken.
Season with salt.
Fold foil and seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serves 6.

title: pasta red duke
directions: Boil pasta.
Heat oil and saute garlic.
Add nuts, tomatoes and basil.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken stock, salt and pepper.
Toss with pasta and serve.

title: taco corn bread
directions: Cook 1 pound hamburg, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serve over corn bread.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Cut heavy duty foil into large squares or use 2 pieces of regular.
Put 1 seasoned hamburger patty on foil.
Add sliced cheese.
Slice 1 potato in thin slices over meat.
Add corn, salsa, butter, salt and pepper.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Make 1 per each family member.
Open and enjoy! No need to fix anything else.
Great for camping.
Put into hot coals until done!

title: company squash casserole
directions: Place squash and onion in enough water to cover and cook until tender.
Drain well, set aside.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour.
Add milk and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in cauliflower and mix well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Steam chicken wings as per instructions on Old Bay seasoning can.
Drain and put in large crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce, salt and pepper with hot sauce (to taste).
Add onions.
Let cook in crock-pot until chicken wings are tender, approximately 2 to 3 hours on low.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Place in center of a pie pan and surround with a ring of chilli.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Chill.
Serve with chips.
Preparation time: 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg until mixture is fluffy.
Blend in pineapple and dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet 3 inches apart.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 20 minutes.
Cookies are better if stored 24 hours.

title: ann's over the coals dinner
directions: You will need a 12 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch foil baking pan.

title: daisy's pumpkin squares
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and stir into ice cream.
Crush beforehand the gingersnaps.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put layer of pumpkin mix and another layer of gingersnaps.
Keep layering.
Freeze.
Top with whipping cream.
Cut into squares. Very good.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar to beaten egg yolks and mix with dates and nuts.
Add flour mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in slow oven (300° to 325°) for approximately 45 minutes or until done when tested.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with raw veggies.
Keep cold. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Make Jell-O from box directions, except instead of 2 cups of water, use 1 and use juice that comes from the strawberries. Refrigerate until thickened.
Fold in strawberries, Cool Whip, nut, pineapple and coconut.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: bob's famous potato soup
directions: Prepare potatoes and set aside in large pot.
Saute onion, celery and carrot in 1/2 stick butter for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add garlic and continue cooking 3 minutes.
Drain potatoes and add to pot.
Barely cover with chicken stock.
Bring to boil and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add green onions and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In another bowl, add 3 ladles hot soup and (temper) 1 pint half and half; stir.
Return mixture to soup pot.
Repeat until desired soup thickness.
Serve hot.
Do not boil after adding the half and half.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasonings. Mix well.
Then stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: pea salad
directions: Thaw peas in colander until well drained. Cook and crumble bacon.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: pastry for pies and tarts(using food processor)
directions: Use steel knife.
Put all ingredients in bowl except ice water.
Cut butter in 7 to 8 pieces.
Process to consistency of coarse meal (5 to 10 seconds) and with machine running, pour in ice water in steady stream.
Ball of dough will form above blade in 20 to 50 seconds.
Remove, cool, flour and roll out.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Then, add wet ingredients.
May keep refrigerated up to 3 days.
For rolls, cut and bake.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: *If canned potatoes, drain; if baked or boiled, peel and mash.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Put in a casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple snacking cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar in large mixing bowl; beat until well mixed.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon; stir.
Add dry ingredients alternately with apples to egg mixture, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and half of butterscotch morsels. Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle batter with remaining morsels.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart casserole.
Mix well. Microwave at High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High for 4 to 11 minutes or until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned, stirring every 2 minutes.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread to 1/4 inch thickness on large, well buttered baking sheet.
Cool until set.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in 3 cups half and half.
Stir constantly over low heat until mixture thickens.
Beat some of the mixture into eggs; beat this into hot sauce in saucepan and stir over low heat for 1 minute. Remove from heat and chill covered.
Gradually stir in 3 cups half and half and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream freezer and churn with salt and ice for approximately 20 minutes.
Add strawberries and churn until hardened.
Allow to ripen for 2 to 3 hours.

title: hungry jack biscuit barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar, white sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Cook 1 minute to blend flavors.
Place 1 biscuit in each muffin cup.
Press in bottom and up sides of muffin cups.
Add about 1/4 cup of meat mixture to each cup. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until edges of biscuits are browned.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Stir baking soda into pulp. Add sugar and eggs. Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and vanilla. Beat well. Add milk and beat well. Add butter and beat well. Bake at 325 degrees for 55 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Bring water and butter to a full boil; remove from heat.
Add cocoa; stir until mixture leaves side of pan and forms ball.
Beat in confectioners sugar and vanilla.

title: soft buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix white sugar and shortening well.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix. Add other ingredients.
Mix. Chill mixture in refrigerator.
Remove from refrigerator when chilled; drop by spoonfuls into flour. Shake off flour and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or so.
Prepare a glaze of powdered sugar, butter, milk and lemon flavoring.
Brush on cookies after baking.

title: p.j.'s gingersnaps
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually, then egg and molasses.
When mixed, gradually add in flour mixture.
Make balls of mixture, then roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Tops will be slightly rounded and crackly.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water; measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour to yeast.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening. Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with cloth; place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, cut off amount needed and return remaining dough to refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Beat butter or margarine until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour again with soda.
Beat into creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixed with vanilla, almond extract and grated orange and lemon peel. (Begin and end with dry ingredients.)
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Allow to cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to continue cooling.
This is very good!!!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Keeps well in freezer for as long as two weeks.

title: cheese log
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature.
Mash and mix with all ingredients, except 1/2 cup pecans and chili powder.
Roll in chili powder on wax paper after you have formed mixture into a log, then roll in the other 1/2 cup pecans.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: hollandaise pickles
directions: Peel and chunk the pickles, measuring 4 quarts.
Soak for 3 hours in salt and ice water or cubes to cover, then drain.
Add onions and put in large kettle to boil; mix well.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour this over pickles.
Boil good for 10 minutes.
After it has started a good boil, stir so it doesn't scorch and can while hot.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: braised oriental mushrooms
directions: Soak mushrooms in 3 to 4 cups boiling water and cover for 15 minutes.
Trim off stems, squeeze out water and cut into bite size pieces.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand a few minutes.
Beat eggs lightly.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture alternately with apple mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until cake tester shows it's done.

title: slow cooker hot dogs
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Slice hot dog skin thinly. Combine all ingredients in slow cooker; stir and heat on low for 4 hours.
Hot dogs can be cut through and used as appetizers or served as is in buns.

title: baked doughnuts
directions: Pour hot milk over shortening, sugar, salt and spices; cool to lukewarm and add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water. Add eggs; stir in flour and beat.
Knead to a smooth dough.
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until very light.
Toss on floured board and pat into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 3-inch cutter and place rings 2 inches apart on buttered baking sheets. Brush with melted butter and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes in oven.
Remove and brush again with melted butter and roll in granulated sugar.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for an additional 15 minutes.
Roll out 1 package crescent rolls into a rectangle.
Cut into strips and lattice on top of casserole.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.
Put 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top and 1/2 can Durkee onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 4 to 6 minutes until onions are golden brown.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Add salt and baking powder; sift three times.
Cream shortening thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually. Cream together until light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with liquid mixture a small amount at a time; beat after each addition. Add flavorings.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 well-greased 9-inch pans in 375° oven 20 minutes.
Prepare filling. Spread on layers; put together.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water as it says and add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
I usually add some chopped pecans.
Good at Thanksgiving.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press 1 package crescent roll dough into bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla; spread on top of dough.
Roll other package of dough to seal seams.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Cool, cut into squares.

title: microwave pizza casserole(serves 5 to 6)
directions: Crumble ground beef in plastic colander which has been placed in a 1-quart glass measurer.
Add chopped onion.

title: grilled fresh tuna
