directions: Brush tuna with oil on both sides. Sprinkle liberally with salt and pepper. Grill 2 to 3 minutes while turning on both sides (center should be pink).

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones and pull into chunks while warm.
Mix with soup, sour cream, milk and seasonings. Put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs and sprinkle on chicken mixture.
Sprinkle liberally with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: I usually add extra seasoning, a bit of salt, a dash of red pepper and some black pepper, to taste.
If you need more liquid, add some oil from artichokes.

title: tamale noodles
directions: Cook stew meat until done (could use hamburger).
Add noodles to meat and broth; add salt to taste.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add corn, tomato sauce and olives.
Season with pepper and chili powder.
Add to cooked meat and noodles and put in casserole.
Add a generous amount of grated cheese over top.
Put in oven and brown.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar thoroughly until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and milk then add flavorings. Blend well.
Grease well a 10 inch tube pan, add cake batter.
Bake in 325 degree oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bugle dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except Bugles with mixer.
Bake at 350° until warm.
Serve warm with Bugles.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Make 1 color at a time.
Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Divide into 2 (1/2) cups.
Add 1/4 cup cold water to one half.
Add 1/4 cup condensed milk to other half.
Pour clear jello into a 7 x 12-inch clear baking dish; chill until firm.
Pour jello with condensed milk on top; chill until firm. Repeat directions, using other flavors of jello and layering one flavor on top of another.
Very pretty.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend together in blender.
Makes 1 pint.

title: amazing impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender. Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: elegant steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces; place in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Add mushrooms.
Blend mushroom soup, sherry and liquid from mushrooms; pour over steak.
Cover and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with egg slices and olives.
Serves 8.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large saucepan and stir to mix well.
Add the water and stir to dissolve the cornstarch.
Add 1 cup berries and cook, stirring constantly over moderate heat, until the sauce is thickened and clear.
Add lemon juice and stir well to mix and cool slightly.
Add 3 cups of fresh berries. Gently transfer the filling to the prepared pie shell.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
This is simply the best blueberry pie you have ever eaten.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas, blending well after each addition. Stir in nuts.

title: frozen coleslaw
directions: Combine salt and cabbage.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze dry. Add carrot.

title: chicken jambalaya au cajun
directions: Season chicken with salt and red pepper; brown in oil.
In another pan, fry onions, celery and bell pepper in a small amount of oil until wilted, not browned.
Add water, chicken bouillon cubes and garlic.
Bring to a boil; continue to boil for 15 minutes.
Add green onions, parsley and raw rice, mixing well. Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover tightly and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pesto pasta *
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in blender.
Mix on hot cooked pasta of your choice.
Gnocchi and cheese tortellini work well, as does fresh peppered cheese ravioli.
Serve with green and red salad and a crusty Italian semolina bread, for a complete meal.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour in crust and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake until knife in center comes out clean, approximately 20 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Sift in flour.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Roll in balls with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pickle sticks
directions: First Day:
In the morning, peel cucumbers and cut out seed. Cut into lengthwise strips.
Cucumbers should weigh 7 pounds after seeded and peeled.
Soak 24 hours in water and lime.

title: taco soup
directions: This serves a bunch, but if you double the recipe it should serve 14.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; blend at high speed for 2 minutes.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and nuts.
Add butter; mix again.
Add undiluted orange juice; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls, coating with additional powdered sugar, if desired.
Yields 4 dozen balls.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Place Boston butt in crock-pot. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over Boston butt. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours. Remove meat from cooker and shred with fork. Coat with barbecue sauce, if desired.

title: tally ho dressing
directions: Beat with mixer for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Put zucchini in covered pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 15 minutes.
Add sugar, boil 6 minutes longer.
Remove from heat, add jello.
Stir well.
Put in prepared jars and seal.
Refrigerate after breaking seal.
Yields 4 qt.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, mix.
Sift soda and flour.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Add apples, pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Do not open oven while cake is baking.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and pat into a cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions.

title: bread
directions: Stir sugar, salt and shortening into scalded milk until dissolved.
Cool
to
lukewarm.
Add to cool mixture.
Add 1/2 of the
flour.
Beat
until
smooth.
Gradually
add remaining flour. Mix well
to
make soft dough.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until
doubled in bulk.
Divide into two equal portions. Place in greased
bread
pans.
Brush loaves with shortening. Cover, let rise
until
double.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about one hour.

title: aunt elvira's lunch box pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and add the next 3 ingredients; let set 3 hours.
Drain and then add last 4 ingredients.
Cook until good and hot (do not boil).
Put in hot jars with lids.
Makes 14 pints.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dice artichokes in a square Pyrex pan. Beat eggs and pour into pan.
Break bread apart and add to pan. Sprinkle some salt and pepper; mix together.
Top with grated cheese (pepperoni is optional).
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until brown.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Drain grease off.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and spice.
Line 9 x 13-inch dish with half of the tortillas; pour meat mixture over tortillas.
Add another layer of tortillas.
Pour soup over top and milk over soup.
Sprinkle cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: spiced brown bread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 6 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, combine flours, sugar, baking soda and pumpkin spice.
Stir in buttermilk until mixture is moist. Fold in raisins.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until pick comes out clean. Remove from pan.
Makes 6 giant muffins.

title: beef tongue
directions: Wash beef tongue.
Cut in half and place in crock-pot.
Add water, tomatoes, salt, black pepper and garlic powder.
Slice onion and place on top of tongue.
Cover and cook for 8 to 10 hours (at 300° approximately) at medium setting.
Tongue should be very tender when done.
Peel when cool.
Slice or shred.
Can be served on flour or corn tortillas sprinkled with picante sauce if desired.

title: potato chip casserole
directions: In large pan, on high heat, fry hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add soup and 1/2 can of milk.
Stir until hot.
Add 1/4 bag of chips.
Stir until moist.
Add rest of the chips slowly and turn down stove to low.
Stir and add milk to keep moist.
Grate cheese over the top.
Cover for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: armenian rolls
directions: Soften the yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water with the sugar.
Sift together the flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in the melted oleo or butter, cooled to lukewarm.
Add a little more lukewarm water, if needed, to make a stiff dough (not too stiff). Add the eggs.
Save 2 tablespoons for glazing.

title: zucchini imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375° or until top is browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Put cooked chicken in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with sour cream and chicken soup mixture.
Spread cracker crumbs and butter mixture over top.
Sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut up into pieces.
Fry chicken pieces in soy sauce until golden brown.
Add chopped onion and celery.
Cover and cook until crunchy (approximately 20 minutes). Add bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Cook until bean sprouts and chestnuts are done.
Thicken with cornstarch and soy sauce mixture.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all together and pour in churn.
Finish filling with sweet milk.
Fruit may be added.

title: pasta bean salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate at least 4 hours, overnight is better.
All of the ingredients can be changed to suit your own taste.
Four bean salad can be used instead, also.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Combine egg, vinegar and water.
Sprinkle over dry ingredients.
Mix with a fork.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out. This will make 2 double pie crusts.
This is good to make up ahead of time and freeze.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and peppers in ground beef until brown.
Drain. Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover for the last 15 minutes.
If dry, add more tomato juice.
May be put in crock-pot on low, 1 to 3 hours.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Place crushed Oreos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve some crumbs for topping.
Cover with softened ice cream.
Spread with chocolate fudge.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts and cookie crumbs.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer shortly before serving.

title: homemade pork sausage
directions: Mix all by hand.
Freeze in packs or patties.

title: mccloud pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Place in a large bowl.
Cover with boiling water.
Cover.
Repeat this process every day for 3 days.
Let stand on the fourth day.
On the fifth day, slice cucumbers and put back in bowl.
Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Pour over sliced cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days.
Drain off liquid.
Bring liquid mixture to a boil.
Pour over pickles which have been put in sterilized jars.
Place on sterilized lids and seal.
Makes 6 half pint jars.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 2 x 1-inch strips and toss with soy sauce.
Brown on one side in oil.
Cut pepper into strips.
Add to meat and stir until meat is browned.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Add to meat mixture.

title: deer steak in mushrooms
directions: Clean deer meat, removing all fat and gristle, leaving only red, lean meat.
Place on cutting board and tenderize by beating with meat mallet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge in flour. Fry in hot oil only until slightly browned on both sides.
After browning all pieces, pour off all except 2 tablespoons oil.
To the oil, add soup, mushrooms and seasonings.
Return meat to this mixture.
Cook, covered, on top of stove for about 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: savory southern chicken pies
directions: In saucepan, brown sausage; drain on paper towels.
Pour off fat and in same pan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook 1 minute more.
Add chicken, sausage and peas; heat through.
Pour into large casserole.

title: salmon bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 450 degrees for 20 minutes or lightly browned. This mixture may also be used to form into patties and fried.

title: cinnamon breakfast cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons melted butter and beaten egg; mix thoroughly.
Gradually blend in milk.
Pour batter into an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle the brown sugar and cinnamon over top; also butter slivers.
Bake in a hot (425°) oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple chili sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and strain off some of the juice.
Add onions, peppers, vinegar, sugar and salt; cook 2 hours.
Add apples, cinnamon and cloves.
Cook until thick.
Makes about 10 pints. May be frozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-fours
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar.
Beat in eggs gradually, one at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Spread 3/4 of batter in a 15 x 10-inch greased and floured cookie sheet.
Spread with 1 can any flavor pie filling.
Dot remaining batter on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together until smooth.
Add melted butter. Stir.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a regular pie crust and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve on crackers, Melba toast or fresh vegetables.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots for 20 minutes and drain. Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs. Add orange juice and sugar mixture. Add dry ingredients and blend well. Stir in apricots and nuts. Bake in a greased and floured pan at 325° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chef's casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown onions and meat in oleo.
Combine all other ingredients and noodles.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Mild tasting.
Very good.
Can be frozen.

title: quick pineapple pie
directions: Blend flour, sugar, eggs and melted oleo.
Add coconut and drained pineapple; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in slow oven for 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: pie crust
directions: In mixing bowl, combine skim milk, extracts and sweetener. Add bread crumbs and stir with fork until crumbs are evenly moistened.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: celery-crabmeat casserole
directions: Cover with slivered almonds and bread crumbs or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza bread
directions: Roll out bread dough (this takes a while working with the dough) to fit a cookie sheet.
Spread salsa on, then layer with hard salami, pepperoni, cheese and peppers (I usually put 2 layers).
Make slits in sides.
Bring up sides on top and pinch together.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: good cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; 12 minutes for crisp.
Makes a big batch.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water gradually.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add lemon juice, nutmeg and butter. Makes 1 cup.

title: holiday date balls
directions: In large heavy saucepan over medium-high heat, cook egg, dates, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt to a thick syrup.
Remove from heat and fold in cereal and nuts.
Cool until comfortable to work with.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in powdered sugar to coat.

title: wassail (hot apple cider and cinnamon)
directions: Pour apple juice into a large pot.
Add cinnamon and cloves; bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat, cover and let cool.

title: sesame seed cheese spread
directions: Cream the cheeses and butter. Add all ingredients except sesame seed and blend. Roast sesame seed in shallow pan at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Watch carefully so they do not burn. Divide cheese mixture and place in 6 crocks (4 ounces each). Sprinkle sesame seed on top. Serve with crackers.
Yields 6 crocks.

title: yeast rolls
directions: *You may want to add another 1/2 cup of sugar, depending on your taste.

title: fried apples
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apples. Bring to a boil, stirring, and cook until it thickens. Add apples; make sure all apples are coated with mixture. Reduce heat and cook until apples are tender. Stir very little so apples will remain intact.

title: kifle
directions: Crumble yeast into flour and cut in butter, like for a piecrust. Add sour cream, beaten egg yolks and rind. Mix well. Roll out dough on powdered sugar. Cut dough into triangles. Fill with nut filling (recipe to follow). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brown on bottom only. Roll cookies in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: baked beans
directions: Inspect beans; wash and cover with water.
Soak overnight. In the morning, drain the beans.
Cover with fresh water; simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse with water.
Scrape and score salt pork.
You may chop onion, or bury it whole in center of beans.
Add remainder of ingredients to beans with enough water to cover.
Top with salt pork.
Bake in a 250° oven for 8 hours.
Add water when necessary.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix with a fork or a pastry blender until all ingredients are moistened.
Then, with hands, mold dough into ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling into desired shape.
Makes 4 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, bacon and cheese in a bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables.
Mix well. Let cool before serving.

title: louisiana neighbor's red beans and rice
directions: Brown butter in bottom of large pot.
Add vegetables and saute until browned.
Add beans and 2 cups of water (or more as needed). Add bay leaves, ham hocks and sausage.
Cook 4 or more hours, stirring occasionally until beans are pasty.
Add water, if needed.
Serve over rice.

title: miss scarlet's atlanta rice pilau
directions: Saute first 2 ingredients together until done. Drain. Set aside. Boil in small amount of water until done the chicken breasts. Save liquid. Chop into small pieces. Prepare according to package directions, using chicken liquid, the rice. Saute in small amount of sausage grease the onion and celery. Mix sausage, chicken, rice and vegetables in large bowl. Add soup and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: haluski
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Steam fry with margarine, 2 or 3 ounces of water, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook noodles are directed on package.
Cut bacon into pieces and fry for bacon chips.
Mix together with cottage cheese and serve.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Shake pieces of chicken with salt and cornstarch.
Stir-fry in hot oil until chicken turns white.
Add mushrooms with liquid, green peppers, water chestnuts and soy sauce.
Cook for 4 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: oprah's no-fat french fries
directions: Rinse potatoes.
Separate egg whites in bowl large enough to dip potatoes in.
Discard yolks.
Beat egg whites slightly.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Place sliced potatoes in egg whites, making sure all sides are coated with egg whites.
Place on sprayed cookie sheet, scattered apart.
Bake at 375° approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn once or twice during baking.
Remove from oven; loosen from pan.
Season to taste.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meats thoroughly.

Soak bread in cream about 5 minutes. Cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender, but not brown. Mix meats, crumb mixture, onion, egg, parsley and seasonings. Beat 5 minutes with mixer until well combined.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Wet hands for easier shaping.
Brown meatballs in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove from skillet.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time. Begin to add flour and milk.
Blend completely.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 10 x 6
x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Add water.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Using 2 knives or a pastry blender, cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Top with ice cream when served if desired.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: rice a roni salad
directions: Prepare rice a roni as directed on box.
Add green olives, green pepper, water chestnuts and artichokes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook
noodles
as
directed
and drain. Mix noodles and tuna with
soup,
salt and pepper.
Place in small casserole. Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker crust for 9-inch pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar in a bowl. Add butter, mix thoroughly. Press mixture firmly and evenly against bottom and sides of pie pan. Bake 10 min., cool; fill with chiffon or cream type filling.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions until well mixed.
Cover; chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir well.
If desired, spoon into round bread bowl.
Serve with cut up vegetables or chips. Try gourmet crackers.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: ziti with creamy herb sauce(easy)
directions: Prepare pasta and drain.
Meanwhile, stir cheeses with parsley and seasonings.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water; stir into cheese mixture.
Pour over pasta; toss to coat.
Serve.

title: vegetable curry dip
directions: Mix well; replace in jar.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Good with all kinds of raw vegetables.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Saute rice in butter for 3 minutes.
Add soup plus one can of water and mushrooms with water.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook on low for 20 minutes.
Good for picnics.

title: ham and potato breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except paprika in large bowl.
Pour into ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 x 2-inch; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fig preserves
directions: Cut stems on figs (not down into fig). Put figs in bowl; sprinkle soda all through boiling water to cover figs. Let set about 30 minutes. Wash 3 or 4 times. Put layer of figs, then layer of sugar and repeat until pot is full. Let set overnight. Boil real slow until about as thick as table syrup, then pour in jars and seal.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with soft tortillas. Brown 1 pound of ground beef (or slightly more); drain.
Place drained meat on top of tortillas.
Cover with beans.
Mix together the Ro-Tel tomatoes and mushroom soup; pour over beans.
Cover top with tortillas.
Slice enough Velveeta cheese to cover everything. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Recipe freezes well and may actually improve flavor.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix alternately with the wet mixture.
Add prunes, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut wings into 3 parts.
Cook tips of wings in saucepan with 1 cup water.
Cook until soft.
Discard tips and reserve broth.

title: hurricane cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut.
Spread evenly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed; pour on top of nut mixture (do not mix).
Beat together margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Drop by teaspoons on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes or until done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix, flour, sugar, shortening, 2 eggs, baking powder, vanilla and salt with a mixer at medium speed. Beat until well mixed.
Shape dough into ball, wrap with waxed paper and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees and lightly grease cookie sheets.
Roll dough out to 1/4 inch thick and cut dough with floured cookie cutters.
Place cookies 1/2 inch apart on cookie sheets.
Brush tops of cookies with egg white mixture and bake for 8 minutes.
Cool cookies on wire racks.

title: pot pie
directions: Cook
chicken
until tender.
Remove from bone; discard skin and
dice meat.
Reserve broth.
Melt margarine in a pan and
stir in
flour.
Add 3 cups broth and the milk.
Cook to sauce consistency.
Place
chicken and vegetables in a large, deep casserole.
Add sauce, salt and pepper;
mix well.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add raisins and nuts.
Stir soda into hot applesauce; add to sugar mixture and then add flour.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and coconut. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: lemony cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes; cool.
Reduce temperature to 300°.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon; mix well.
Spread preserves evenly over prepared crust.
Pour cheese mixture over preserves.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pickled beets
directions: In a medium saucepan combine vinegar, sugar, water, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally; add sliced beets.
Return to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool, then chill in liquid 8 hours or overnight.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: jiffy spanish rice
directions: In 3-quart casserole, crumble beef.

Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. Drain. Add rice, tomatoes, onion, chili powder, salt and pepper. Cover and microwave on High 8 to 11 minutes. Stir halfway through cooking. Stir well.
Let stand, covered, about 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach-almond ice cream
directions: Heat milk in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar and egg yolks; beat well.
Stir about 1/4 of hot milk into yolk mixture.
Return to remaining hot milk; stir well.
Stir in Amaretto; cook over low heat about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, or until mixture is no longer frothy and begins to curdle.
Remove from heat; cover and chill at least 2 hours. Place half of peach slices in container of an electric blender; blend until pureed.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Repeat with remaining peach slices; stir in lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar. Add chilled custard and whipping cream; beat at low speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into freezer can of a 5-quart hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen about 1 hour.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: wellesley fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water over low heat, stirring until smooth. Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Cool until lukewarm.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in remaining sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate mixture.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans before removing.

title: lemon-lime slush punch
directions: Mix the lime jello and sugar and dissolve with 7 cups of water, then add 6 more cups of water.
After mixing well, add the ReaLemon juice and pineapple juice.
Pour mixture into several containers to freeze solid.
To serve, thaw to slush by adding 2 or 3 bottles of ginger ale.

title: roquefort chicken
directions: Brown chicken; put in 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Stir cheese, garlic and sour cream into pan drippings in skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until heated thoroughly. Do not let mixture boil.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, salt and water until dissolved; add syrup and cook until soft ball stage.
Add 1/2 to egg whites, beaten until stiff with cream of tartar.
Continue beating while adding syrup.
Cook remaining syrup to hard crack stage and add to egg white mixture. Add vanilla and nuts (optional).
Beat until it begins to lose its gloss, then pour in pan and cut or drop on wax paper.

title: pot roast stew
directions: Use large pot.
Put flour and pepper on wax paper; roll pot roast until covered.
Brown on high heat all sides with chopped onion.
Add beef broth, bay leaf and spices and simmer for 2 hours. Add carrots and cook for 1 hour.
Add potatoes to cook for 20 minutes.
Add string beans to cook for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Put in Jell-O mold.
Especially good with chicken or turkey.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat and garlic.
Stir in flour and egg and cook until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for an hour.
Roll into balls and freeze overnight.
Roll balls into flour and milk mixture (1 cup each) and then into cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: san francisco chicken
directions: Split each chicken breast and pepper well.
Blend bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and salt with fork.
Melt butter and press garlic into it.
Simmer gently for 3 to 5 minutes.
Dip each piece of chicken into it (butter mix), then into bread crumb mixture. Roll up each piece tightly and fasten with toothpick or small skewer.
Place in buttered baking dish; sprinkle lemon juice, the remaining butter mixture and a dash of paprika.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in raisins, if using. Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix with pumpkin mixture until moistened.
Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam.
Divide mixture into 2 loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until toothpick comes clean when inserted in middle.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mom's red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste with red food coloring and cocoa.
Set aside. Mix soda and vinegar, set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar, and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately and slowly, then add coloring mixture, soda and vinegar mixture, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes. Bake in 3 layers (greased and floured pans).

title: beth's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and ginger in saucepan and heat.
Beat eggs.
Add Pet milk or cream and milk.
Add pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Pour in unbaked large pie shell. Cook for 10 minutes at 450°, then lower oven to 350° and cook for 40 minutes.

title: bernie's brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix thoroughly the peanuts, sugar and syrup.
Place in microwave 8 minutes at high temperature.
After 4 minutes, stir and turn container around.
Cook 4 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from microwave, add baking soda, stir rapidly.
Pour and spread on foil lined pan. Place in refrigerator to speed cooling.
When brittle has cooled, break into pieces.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 1 minute after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put half of bread cubes in a greased baking dish.
Mix chicken, celery and onion with mayonnaise.
Spread over bread in dish.
Top with remaining bread.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over chicken and bread.
Chill overnight.
One hour before serving, add chicken soup and top with grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: save a marriage cheesecake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and chocolate chips.
Pour into crust(s).
Bake 60 to 65 minutes. Refrigerate overnight.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in pot and bring to a boil.
Cool. Slice enough cucumbers to make a gallon.
Slice onions thin, mix with cucumbers and pack in gallon jar.
Pour cooled mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Will be ready to eat in two weeks.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 year.

title: sausage corn chowder
directions: Cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown.
Drain.
In Dutch oven, add to sausage and onion the potatoes, water, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add 2 cans of corn and milk.
Heat through.
Serves 6.
Delicious.

title: apple butter and pear cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Spread brown sugar mixture into bottom of prepared pan. Cut pear halves into 6 slices.
Arrange on top of brown sugar mixture.

title: grandma's thunder cake
directions: Cream together, one at a time, the shortening, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Beat whites until stiff.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Add 1 cup of cold water and 1/3 cup mashed tomatoes.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oil in skillet, add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion and garlic are tender but not browned.
Add ground beef and cook slowly, stirring occasionally until beef loses red color.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, seasonings and sugar.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes or until sauce is thick but not dry.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, blend in ricotta cheese.
In a greased 2 quart casserole, layer half of meat sauce, 3 lasagna noodles, half of ricotta cheese and half of mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers of noodles, ricotta and mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle on parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serves 9.

title: macadamia nut and white chocolate cookies
directions: Cover 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or aluminum foil; set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt into a medium bowl; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer on low speed, beat butter for 30 to 45 seconds, or until butter is creamy.
Gradually add brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat on medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes, or until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well between each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans and peas. Add chopped pimento, celery, pepper and onion rings.
Heat sugar and vinegar.
Cool. Add salt and Wesson oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator. Drain before serving. This will keep several days after it has been marinated.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: braised bear steak
directions: Pound flour and seasonings into the steak with edge of plate or a meat pounder.
Brown onions in bacon fat and add meat.
Brown well on all sides.
Add part of the broth and wine; bring to a boil.
Cook briskly for 5 minutes.
Turn the steak, reduce the heat and cover the pan.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, adding more liquid if necessary.
When steak is tender, remove it to a hot platter.
Add the tomato paste and additional liquid if needed to pan juices to make a smooth sauce.
Taste for seasoning and pour over the steak.
Surround with boiled potatoes, garnish with parsley and serve with sauteed mushrooms.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat deep fryer to 375°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls into grease and cook until brown.

title: strawberry cool whip pie
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk with lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Puree one pint of strawberries in blender.
Combine pureed strawberries with Cool Whip mixture.
Gently blend until well mixed.
Pour into pie crusts and decorate with the remaining pint of strawberries.
Cool.
May freeze if desired.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soften yeast in water in large bowl.
Add sugar and salt to mixture.
Mix in flour, kneading until soft and smooth.
Do not let rise.
Cut immediately into smaller pieces.
Roll into ropes and make pretzel shapes.
Dust foil-lined cookie sheet with flour. Put pretzels on it.
Brush with 1 beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Pour into 3 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, and salt into large bowl. Add brown sugar and mix well.
Blend in eggs and butter; mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Spread into a well greased 11 x 7 inch or 9 x 9 inch pan.

title: beef-bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and celery in skillet until no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Drain grease. Mix baked beans with beef mixture. Pour into greased 2 qt. casserole dish. Top with thawed hash brown potatoes. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned. Top with cheese. Bake another 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Beat together brown sugar, oil and egg.
Add sour milk or buttermilk, soda, salt, vanilla and flour.
Add rhubarb and nuts.

title: heart smart oat bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add liquids.
Stir until moistened.
Place into greased muffin pan or use muffin cups.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: perfection salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add pinch of salt, crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup nuts.
Partially jell.
Mix cup mayonnaise and small cottage cheese.
Add 1 cup evaporated milk. Mix all together.
Pour into mold.

title: neva's fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit.

title: pink party salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with mayonnaise and sugar.
Add cranberry sauce and mix until smooth.
Add undrained pineapple and nuts, mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line muffin cups with paper liners.
Fill with salad mix.
Place in freezer.
When frozen, remove from muffin tins and place in plastic bag.
Keeps well in freezer 2 months.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place pie crust in 9-inch pie dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour into pie dish.
Cover with top crust.
Cut 3 or 4 slits in top of crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Melt margarine and saute potatoes, onion, carrots and celery for 10 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes and simmer for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: chilli
directions: Brown meat, drain and add with remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Let simmer several hours.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours. Serve garnished with popcorn.

title: feed the crowd casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Mix cooked noodles, hamburger, onion, soups, sour cream and corn in a casserole dish. Put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
